1
00:00:00,047 --> 00:00:01,177
- Who says I won't come?
- That's right.

2
00:00:01,177 --> 00:00:02,547
I'm right here.

3
00:00:02,747 --> 00:00:04,647
- Have you guys been well?
- Yes.

4
00:00:04,887 --> 00:00:07,917
We sent Shin Dong cheerful words last week. He watched it.

5
00:00:08,317 --> 00:00:10,617
(While taking time off work,)

6
00:00:10,617 --> 00:00:12,457
(I hope Shin Dong dates someone. From Kyung Hoon)

7
00:00:12,927 --> 00:00:15,297
(The second period without Shin Dong is meaningless. From Soo Geun)

8
00:00:15,497 --> 00:00:17,597
(On exciting Saturdays,)

9
00:00:17,597 --> 00:00:18,967
(we need Shin Dong.)

10
00:00:19,627 --> 00:00:21,327
(Shin Dong, come back soon.)

11
00:00:21,467 --> 00:00:23,767
Shin Dong was touched and sent us a video letter.

12
00:00:23,767 --> 00:00:25,367
- Where is he? Hey, Shin Dong.
- Hey.

13
00:00:25,367 --> 00:00:27,107
Look at him. He seems much better now.

14
00:00:27,107 --> 00:00:29,337
- Exactly.
- Everyone, are you doing well?

15
00:00:29,337 --> 00:00:30,707
I've been doing great.

16
00:00:30,707 --> 00:00:32,207
Don't worry about me.

17
00:00:32,207 --> 00:00:33,977
I will be back on the show soon.

18
00:00:33,977 --> 00:00:35,547
Please wait for Senior Dong.

19
00:00:35,547 --> 00:00:37,177
I'll appear in Part Two very soon.

20
00:00:37,177 --> 00:00:38,787
Guys, I'll be right back.

21
00:00:39,987 --> 00:00:41,787
What? He got his eyebrows tattooed.

22
00:00:42,257 --> 00:00:43,757
Will he perhaps show up later in the second period today?

23
00:00:43,757 --> 00:00:44,887
He looks better now.

24
00:00:44,887 --> 00:00:46,887
- Indeed. Right?
- Shin Dong, come back soon.

25
00:00:46,887 --> 00:00:48,727
Shin Dong, I won't be your partner. So come back.

26
00:00:48,727 --> 00:00:50,227
- He needs to rest now.
- It's more tiring than you think.

27
00:00:50,227 --> 00:00:51,667
- No one listens to him.
- Hwang Soo Kyung.

28
00:00:51,667 --> 00:00:52,727
- What?
- Soo Kyung found it stressful too.

29
00:00:52,727 --> 00:00:54,097
- What was that?
- It's Yoon Su Il's song.

30
00:00:54,097 --> 00:00:55,837
- What's going on?
- Is that an automatic door?

31
00:00:55,837 --> 00:00:56,837
- What? Oh, my.
- My goodness.

32
00:00:57,597 --> 00:00:59,107
- Who ordered Winter Games?
- Seong Jae is here.

33
00:00:59,107 --> 00:01:00,767
- Who ordered Winter Games?
- Did any of you order Winter Games?

34
00:01:00,767 --> 00:01:02,077
Oh, my. What's going on?

35
00:01:02,077 --> 00:01:03,537
- We ordered it.
- What did we order?

36
00:01:03,537 --> 00:01:04,877
Hey, newlywed groom.

37
00:01:05,107 --> 00:01:06,307
Seong Jae is here.

38
00:01:06,307 --> 00:01:07,747
A newlywed groom and a newlywed bride are here.

39
00:01:07,747 --> 00:01:08,817
(The transfer students came as the Winter Games began.)

40
00:01:08,917 --> 00:01:10,647
- Oh, Seung Hi is here too.
- The gold medalist is here.

41
00:01:10,647 --> 00:01:11,647
Hi.

42
00:01:11,647 --> 00:01:12,987
- Hey, Yoon Gy.
- Yoon Gy.

43
00:01:12,987 --> 00:01:14,487
- We see you too often.
- Yoon Gy...

44
00:01:14,487 --> 00:01:15,687
- Yoon Gy has come here before.
- It hasn't been so long.

45
00:01:15,687 --> 00:01:17,957
Seong Jae and Seung Hi have never been here before.

46
00:01:17,957 --> 00:01:18,957
- That's right.
- That's right.

47
00:01:18,957 --> 00:01:20,287
From which school did you transfer?

48
00:01:20,287 --> 00:01:23,557
Hi. We're from United Through Sports High School.

49
00:01:23,557 --> 00:01:25,827
My voice is my only talent. I'm Bae Seong Jae.

50
00:01:25,827 --> 00:01:26,927
- Oh, my.
- He has a great voice.

51
00:01:26,927 --> 00:01:28,337
I became busier after retiring.

52
00:01:28,337 --> 00:01:30,467
I'm the gold medal level that girl, Park Seung Hi.

53
00:01:30,667 --> 00:01:32,637
- Park Seung Hi.
- I'm Kwak Yoon Gy,

54
00:01:32,637 --> 00:01:33,707
the master of celebration move.

55
00:01:34,767 --> 00:01:35,807
(The perfect transfer students for the Winter Games theme)

56
00:01:35,807 --> 00:01:38,507
Yoon Gy, you seem strange with that hair color.

57
00:01:38,507 --> 00:01:40,007
Can you go and dye your hair again?

58
00:01:40,007 --> 00:01:41,617
Why didn't you prepare a wig for me?

59
00:01:41,617 --> 00:01:43,147
- Exactly.
- That was his signature hair color.

60
00:01:43,147 --> 00:01:44,547
- That's right.
- They all are Soo Geun's friends.

61
00:01:44,547 --> 00:01:46,287
- That's right.
- Really?

62
00:01:46,447 --> 00:01:48,087
I worked with Seong Jae and Seung Hi.

63
00:01:48,087 --> 00:01:50,087
And Yoon Gy is a member of the SPC.

64
00:01:50,087 --> 00:01:51,657
- Oh, small...
- What does SPC stand for?

65
00:01:51,657 --> 00:01:52,657
- He's the smartest one.
- Small People Club.

66
00:01:52,657 --> 00:01:54,557
- Oh, SPC?
- Small People Club.

67
00:01:54,997 --> 00:01:57,397
You worked with Seong Jae for a long time.

68
00:01:57,397 --> 00:01:59,497
- For over four years.
- Oh, "Shooting Stars?"

69
00:01:59,497 --> 00:02:00,497
- That's right.
- I commentated on games...

70
00:02:00,497 --> 00:02:01,797
- in which Seung Hi played.
- He contributed a lot to the show.

71
00:02:01,797 --> 00:02:03,997
- That's right.
- We were on the show together.

72
00:02:03,997 --> 00:02:06,437
Yes. On "Shooting Stars," Soo Geun and I...

73
00:02:06,437 --> 00:02:07,937
- You've been working together.
- commentated on games together.

74
00:02:07,937 --> 00:02:11,547
Among all those whom I worked with as a sportscaster,

75
00:02:11,547 --> 00:02:12,807
he's most comfortable to work with.

76
00:02:12,807 --> 00:02:13,847
- Really?
- What's the reason?

77
00:02:13,847 --> 00:02:16,277
- In what aspect?
- He worked very hard...

78
00:02:16,277 --> 00:02:18,047
- as a commentator.
- That's right.

79
00:02:18,047 --> 00:02:19,447
He kept making a prediction.

80
00:02:19,447 --> 00:02:21,147
"I think they will score a goal this time."

81
00:02:21,147 --> 00:02:22,657
- But they didn't.
- Wait. He made predictions?

82
00:02:22,657 --> 00:02:24,117
- Did he bet money on the games?
- No.

83
00:02:24,117 --> 00:02:25,627
I make predictions because I take after my mom.

84
00:02:25,627 --> 00:02:27,257
Oh, that's right. His mother is...

85
00:02:27,257 --> 00:02:28,927
- a great shaman.
- It's because of shamanism.

86
00:02:29,527 --> 00:02:31,197
- "Because of shamanism?"
- That's not true.

87
00:02:31,197 --> 00:02:33,127
Rain believes in "Rainism" while I believe in shamanism.

88
00:02:33,827 --> 00:02:36,367
Shamanism

89
00:02:36,967 --> 00:02:40,607
How long has Seong Jae been working freelance?

90
00:02:40,837 --> 00:02:43,537
I've been a freelancer for five years.

91
00:02:43,537 --> 00:02:44,537
- It's been a long time.
- That long?

92
00:02:44,537 --> 00:02:45,847
- I'm a little upset with him.
- Oh, I see.

93
00:02:45,847 --> 00:02:47,947
It's very common for an announcer to appear on Men on a Mission...

94
00:02:47,947 --> 00:02:49,447
- after going freelance.
- That's right.

95
00:02:49,447 --> 00:02:50,977
- Right.
- I'm sure...

96
00:02:50,977 --> 00:02:52,817
- he hated to see one of us.
- That makes sense.

97
00:02:52,817 --> 00:02:54,917
- Why didn't you come on the show?
- To be honest,

98
00:02:55,117 --> 00:02:56,717
all of you made me feel like it was too much for me.

99
00:02:57,287 --> 00:02:58,757
Especially Yeong Cheol...

100
00:02:58,757 --> 00:03:00,057
- Me?
- drained my energy...

101
00:03:00,057 --> 00:03:01,997
- whenever I met him.
- Oh, really?

102
00:03:01,997 --> 00:03:03,457
I'm a bit of a quiet type.

103
00:03:03,457 --> 00:03:05,327
- Both Yeong Cheol and Soo Geun...
- Right.

104
00:03:05,327 --> 00:03:06,967
- drained all my energy.
- I see.

105
00:03:06,967 --> 00:03:08,497
I needed to rest in the bed for two days.

106
00:03:08,497 --> 00:03:09,837
We shared a green room as well.

107
00:03:09,837 --> 00:03:11,367
Because Seong Jae said he hated working with me,

108
00:03:11,367 --> 00:03:13,267
- I had to leave the show.
- That's not true.

109
00:03:13,737 --> 00:03:15,237
- Is that why you left the show?
- He seemed happy when I quit.

110
00:03:15,237 --> 00:03:16,377
- I heard that.
- That's not true.

111
00:03:16,377 --> 00:03:17,977
- I cried.
- I quit overnight after five years.

112
00:03:17,977 --> 00:03:20,147
No. I cried when I heard you would quit.

113
00:03:20,147 --> 00:03:21,577
So the rumor that Seong Jae influenced his decision was true.

114
00:03:21,577 --> 00:03:23,047
- No. That's not true.
- Exactly.

115
00:03:23,047 --> 00:03:25,017
I text Soo Geun often...

116
00:03:25,017 --> 00:03:26,047
- to say I miss him.
- I know.

117
00:03:26,047 --> 00:03:27,747
- To say sorry to him?
- No, not that.

118
00:03:27,747 --> 00:03:29,957
- To say that I miss him.
- "I'm sorry I made you quit."

119
00:03:29,957 --> 00:03:32,627
- No. I swear that it's not true.
- "I'm sorry I got you fired."

120
00:03:32,627 --> 00:03:34,287
What did you like about him?

121
00:03:34,287 --> 00:03:35,897
- And what did you hate about him?
- You mean, Soo Geun?

122
00:03:35,897 --> 00:03:37,127
- Tell us one at a time.
- He got him.

123
00:03:37,127 --> 00:03:38,157
- What did you like about him?
- Soo Geun?

124
00:03:38,157 --> 00:03:39,227
You got him fired because he drained your energy.

125
00:03:39,227 --> 00:03:40,767
- Seong Jae said they should...
- Exactly. Now...

126
00:03:40,767 --> 00:03:42,037
- fire one of him and Soo Geun.
- No.

127
00:03:42,037 --> 00:03:43,137
- Stay calm.
- That's not true.

128
00:03:43,137 --> 00:03:44,967
They won't stop until you say he made you uncomfortable.

129
00:03:44,967 --> 00:03:46,007
- This will end only if you say so.
- But I mean...

130
00:03:46,007 --> 00:03:48,007
- Right. Let's end this.
- Right.

131
00:03:48,007 --> 00:03:49,177
I didn't say anything.

132
00:03:49,177 --> 00:03:51,277
When I met the director, I made this gesture.

133
00:03:52,007 --> 00:03:53,107
- Oh, I see.
- "Fire him."

134
00:03:53,107 --> 00:03:54,477
- You made that gesture?
- This gesture would be enough...

135
00:03:54,477 --> 00:03:55,947
- to fire someone. Absolutely.
- It's done now.

136
00:03:55,947 --> 00:03:57,277
- I gave a hand signal.
- You didn't have to say anything.

137
00:03:57,277 --> 00:03:58,647
I didn't want to speak on the phone to avoid leaving proof.

138
00:03:58,647 --> 00:04:00,517
You two won the Best Couple Award...

139
00:04:00,517 --> 00:04:02,087
- and worked together for long.
- Yes.

140
00:04:02,087 --> 00:04:04,517
Did you know he was in a relationship?

141
00:04:04,987 --> 00:04:06,587
I knew that.

142
00:04:06,587 --> 00:04:07,927
- You knew?
- What?

143
00:04:08,357 --> 00:04:10,457
- I heard no one knew.
- Seung Hi, did you know?

144
00:04:10,457 --> 00:04:11,997
- Actually...
- You didn't know, Soo Geun?

145
00:04:11,997 --> 00:04:14,467
Seong Jae created quite a twist.

146
00:04:14,467 --> 00:04:15,867
- Right.
- When we worked together,

147
00:04:15,867 --> 00:04:17,537
you spoke badly of your wife.

148
00:04:17,537 --> 00:04:18,737
When did I do that?

149
00:04:18,737 --> 00:04:20,007
Did he speak badly of his wife?

150
00:04:20,007 --> 00:04:22,907
He criticized her soccer skills and said she didn't practice enough.

151
00:04:22,907 --> 00:04:24,377
- Right. You told me that.
- Right. He told me such things.

152
00:04:24,377 --> 00:04:26,077
- Really?
- On a cold winter day...

153
00:04:26,077 --> 00:04:27,377
- I said, - He criticized her soccer skills?

154
00:04:27,377 --> 00:04:31,247
"We should keep her on our team..."

155
00:04:31,247 --> 00:04:33,117
- "even though she's not skillful."
- You didn't know about them.

156
00:04:33,117 --> 00:04:34,987
- Wait. Hold on.
- When I said she should play,

157
00:04:34,987 --> 00:04:37,187
he said we shouldn't let her play because she's not good at it.

158
00:04:37,517 --> 00:04:38,527
- Unlike those words he said...
- Yes?

159
00:04:38,527 --> 00:04:40,187
- So you didn't know about them?
- In front of us,

160
00:04:40,457 --> 00:04:42,057
he criticized his wife,

161
00:04:42,057 --> 00:04:43,697
but he was being all lovey-dovey with her behind our backs.

162
00:04:44,297 --> 00:04:45,897
"You understand why I had to act like that, right?"

163
00:04:45,897 --> 00:04:47,227
- That's what he did then.
- Then his wife...

164
00:04:47,227 --> 00:04:48,637
- It was a smokescreen strategy.
- That means...

165
00:04:48,637 --> 00:04:50,367
- he was seeing her even then?
- He deceived us. Yes.

166
00:04:50,367 --> 00:04:52,337
When I was with the others... How should I put it?

167
00:04:52,337 --> 00:04:53,667
- Right.
- I'm getting choked up.

168
00:04:53,667 --> 00:04:54,907
I had no idea.

169
00:04:54,907 --> 00:04:55,907
- He's flustered.
- I tried not to let it show.

170
00:04:55,907 --> 00:04:57,107
One time, during a soccer game,

171
00:04:57,107 --> 00:04:58,747
- she fell hard.
- Right.

172
00:04:58,747 --> 00:05:00,307
Since I have a lot of experience as a sportscaster,

173
00:05:00,307 --> 00:05:02,847
when I see a player falling down,

174
00:05:02,847 --> 00:05:05,017
I can tell whether or not the player can continue playing.

175
00:05:05,017 --> 00:05:06,747
When I saw her falling down,

176
00:05:06,747 --> 00:05:09,387
- I thought she shouldn't play.
- You didn't care...

177
00:05:09,387 --> 00:05:10,617
if the other players fell down or not.

178
00:05:10,617 --> 00:05:12,627
- Back then, Seong Jae...
- Exactly. I played full-time.

179
00:05:12,627 --> 00:05:13,887
- You played full-time?
- He didn't care about Seung Hi.

180
00:05:13,887 --> 00:05:15,227
When he said she should be helpful to the team...

181
00:05:15,227 --> 00:05:16,797
You said when he criticized her,

182
00:05:16,797 --> 00:05:18,227
you talked badly of her too.

183
00:05:18,227 --> 00:05:20,167
I talked badly of her too, of course.

184
00:05:20,497 --> 00:05:22,337
I feel bad... I'm sorry, Da Yeong.

185
00:05:22,337 --> 00:05:24,067
I did that because I didn't know about them.

186
00:05:24,067 --> 00:05:25,137
- But...
- So that's why he got you fired.

187
00:05:25,137 --> 00:05:26,637
- He hosted a radio show and all.
- Oh, you're right.

188
00:05:26,637 --> 00:05:28,637
- He was very busy then.
- "How dare he criticize my wife?"

189
00:05:28,637 --> 00:05:29,877
- That's probably why he did this.
- "I'll get him fired."

190
00:05:29,877 --> 00:05:31,637
- He was the same as Kyung Hoon.
- He had a reason.

191
00:05:31,637 --> 00:05:33,007
- We didn't know about him either.
- Right.

192
00:05:33,007 --> 00:05:36,217
- Right. We had no idea.
- His wife would sit over there.

193
00:05:36,777 --> 00:05:38,787
They must've given each other a lot of signals secretly.

194
00:05:38,787 --> 00:05:40,317
- We really had no idea.
- That must've been so fun.

195
00:05:40,317 --> 00:05:42,457
He danced so passionately then.

196
00:05:43,117 --> 00:05:44,387
You know that, right?

197
00:05:44,717 --> 00:05:45,927
Think of how different he was...

198
00:05:45,927 --> 00:05:47,387
- when his wife was here.
- Really?

199
00:05:47,387 --> 00:05:49,297
- Seriously, none of us knew.
- None of us knew.

200
00:05:49,297 --> 00:05:50,857
- But now...
- None of us knew. Really.

201
00:05:50,857 --> 00:05:52,397
- Exactly.
- Back then,

202
00:05:52,397 --> 00:05:53,667
- I was trying to impress her.
- We didn't know.

203
00:05:53,667 --> 00:05:55,667
(I was trying to impress her.)

204
00:05:55,667 --> 00:05:57,067
That's why I danced passionately.

205
00:05:57,237 --> 00:05:59,737
- Yoon Gy, it's awkward.
- Now you only dance professionally?

206
00:05:59,737 --> 00:06:01,877
- Give Soo Geun your transfer form.
- Okay.

207
00:06:01,877 --> 00:06:03,377
- Right.
- Right.

208
00:06:03,377 --> 00:06:05,647
- We haven't met Yoon Gy in a while.
- Right.

209
00:06:05,647 --> 00:06:07,007
I feel most comfortable around you.

210
00:06:07,007 --> 00:06:08,717
- Right, Yoon Gy?
- We have the same eye level.

211
00:06:08,717 --> 00:06:09,847
Exactly.

212
00:06:09,847 --> 00:06:12,217
- Yoon Gy, let's hurry up and go.
- What?

213
00:06:12,387 --> 00:06:14,547
(Imitating skating sounds)

214
00:06:14,547 --> 00:06:15,557
Come on.

215
00:06:15,857 --> 00:06:16,857
Here you go.

216
00:06:16,857 --> 00:06:18,687
(Combined)

217
00:06:18,987 --> 00:06:20,157
I remember that.

218
00:06:20,427 --> 00:06:22,257
- Yoon Gy told us before.
- Right, he did.

219
00:06:22,257 --> 00:06:23,757
- He could see behind him...
- You see...

220
00:06:23,757 --> 00:06:25,927
- He said he could see the face.
- That's right.

221
00:06:25,927 --> 00:06:28,267
- That was a long time ago.
- Seeing Soo Geun with Yoon Gy,

222
00:06:28,267 --> 00:06:29,997
Soo Geun seemed very tall.

223
00:06:29,997 --> 00:06:31,767
- I told you so.
- Exactly.

224
00:06:31,767 --> 00:06:33,407
- Among small people...
- Is Soo Geun taller than me?

225
00:06:33,407 --> 00:06:34,967
- Of course.
- Hey.

226
00:06:34,967 --> 00:06:36,277
- How tall are you?
- I can't believe him.

227
00:06:36,477 --> 00:06:37,807
- Your height...
- How tall are you, Soo Geun?

228
00:06:37,807 --> 00:06:39,177
- Stand next to each other.
- I'm 165cm tall.

229
00:06:39,477 --> 00:06:41,577
- He's a bit taller than me.
- Right. He's taller than you.

230
00:06:41,577 --> 00:06:42,817
- Come over here.
- He seemed much taller than you.

231
00:06:42,817 --> 00:06:44,777
- Soo Geun seems taller than him.
- Soo Geun is much taller than him.

232
00:06:44,777 --> 00:06:45,787
I'm much taller than him.

233
00:06:45,787 --> 00:06:47,417
- Do you want to keep your shoes on?
- He seems taller than you.

234
00:06:47,787 --> 00:06:50,317
- Walk past me.
- That's okay. I can feel it.

235
00:06:50,317 --> 00:06:52,327
- Right? You can feel it, don't you?
- Don't come near him.

236
00:06:52,327 --> 00:06:53,587
I can feel the difference even from afar.

237
00:06:53,587 --> 00:06:54,627
- You can feel it?
- Hey.

238
00:06:54,627 --> 00:06:56,427
- Gosh. I'm dumbfounded.
- He looks much taller than you.

239
00:06:56,427 --> 00:06:59,327
- Hey, I hang out with Jang Hoon.
- Wait. But this is...

240
00:06:59,327 --> 00:07:01,367
- There's a big difference.
- Will you be okay?

241
00:07:01,367 --> 00:07:02,667
We can stand side by side to be compared.

242
00:07:02,667 --> 00:07:03,897
There's no difference.

243
00:07:03,897 --> 00:07:05,437
- I see no difference now.
- They're almost the same height.

244
00:07:05,437 --> 00:07:08,407
No. That's because of their hairstyles.

245
00:07:08,407 --> 00:07:10,137
- Soo Geun is taller than him.
- They're the same height.

246
00:07:10,137 --> 00:07:11,947
But I have good body proportions.

247
00:07:12,947 --> 00:07:13,977
- As for body proportions...
- We both are small.

248
00:07:13,977 --> 00:07:16,247
But your legs are this short.

249
00:07:16,247 --> 00:07:17,647
- Check out my waist.
- But...

250
00:07:17,647 --> 00:07:19,347
Your waist is down here.

251
00:07:19,347 --> 00:07:20,347
(The secret to his victory is his long legs.)

252
00:07:20,347 --> 00:07:22,157
- Those small guys are so funny.
- Soo Geun really is taller than me.

253
00:07:22,157 --> 00:07:25,627
- Soo Geun's legs...
- But you have such muscular legs.

254
00:07:26,227 --> 00:07:28,057
Why would we compare our heights?

255
00:07:28,057 --> 00:07:29,797
- It's pointless.
- Indeed.

256
00:07:29,797 --> 00:07:32,497
- It's completely pointless, right?
- Yes.

257
00:07:32,497 --> 00:07:34,697
The transfer form to Men on a Mission.

258
00:07:34,697 --> 00:07:37,337
Names, Bae Seong Jae, Kwak Yoon Gy, and Park Seung Hi.

259
00:07:37,337 --> 00:07:39,007
Welcome!

260
00:07:39,467 --> 00:07:41,207
- It's good to see you again.
- It's nice to meet you all.

261
00:07:41,207 --> 00:07:43,007
First up is the peer relations.

262
00:07:43,207 --> 00:07:45,507
It says they met one another through sports commentary.

263
00:07:45,507 --> 00:07:46,707
- Through sports commentary.
- Do both of you...

264
00:07:46,707 --> 00:07:47,947
have a connection with Seong Jae?

265
00:07:47,947 --> 00:07:49,477
- Can you explain to us?
- Yes. Seung Hi and I commentated...

266
00:07:49,477 --> 00:07:52,647
on the short track games at the Beijing Winter Games.

267
00:07:52,647 --> 00:07:54,247
And I'll work with Yoon Gy this time.

268
00:07:54,847 --> 00:07:57,617
We'll commentate on short track games in Milan.

269
00:07:57,617 --> 00:07:59,287
- So you'll go to Milan?
- Yes.

270
00:07:59,287 --> 00:08:00,557
I guess he's not just good at commentating on soccer games.

271
00:08:00,557 --> 00:08:02,657
- He's good with every sport.
- I found out...

272
00:08:02,657 --> 00:08:04,427
that Seong Jae was a sportscaster,

273
00:08:04,427 --> 00:08:06,927
- and the others are commentators.
- We're commentators.

274
00:08:06,927 --> 00:08:09,967
Is there a big difference between those two?

275
00:08:09,967 --> 00:08:13,307
A sportscaster adds liveliness to a sports commentary...

276
00:08:13,307 --> 00:08:14,567
- by describing the situations.
- That's right.

277
00:08:14,567 --> 00:08:17,007
And commentators who used to be great athletes...

278
00:08:17,007 --> 00:08:18,577
use their expert knowledge...

279
00:08:18,577 --> 00:08:20,177
- to analyze the situations.
- They provide analysis.

280
00:08:20,177 --> 00:08:22,077
- We explain what's happening.
- That's right.

281
00:08:22,077 --> 00:08:23,317
- We also provide information...
- So you...

282
00:08:23,317 --> 00:08:24,547
- about players.
- Basically...

283
00:08:24,547 --> 00:08:26,247
I'll give you a simple example.

284
00:08:26,247 --> 00:08:28,617
For example, which one would say,

285
00:08:28,617 --> 00:08:31,287
"Min Kyung Hoon passed the ball to Kim Hee Chul?"

286
00:08:31,887 --> 00:08:34,027
- That'd be Seong Jae.
- A sportscaster would say that.

287
00:08:34,887 --> 00:08:36,657
"In a situation like that,"

288
00:08:36,757 --> 00:08:38,727
"you shouldn't pass the ball in that direction."

289
00:08:38,727 --> 00:08:40,027
- Right.
- A commentator would say that.

290
00:08:40,027 --> 00:08:41,597
- So an expert explains...
- Right.

291
00:08:41,597 --> 00:08:44,467
Oh, that's why Jang Hoon is the commentator on "Divorce Camp."

292
00:08:44,467 --> 00:08:45,907
- Gosh, seriously.
- He's an expert.

293
00:08:46,007 --> 00:08:48,207
- Park Ha Sun and the others...
- That's a precise comparison.

294
00:08:48,207 --> 00:08:49,637
- I see. I get it now.
- You see...

295
00:08:49,777 --> 00:08:50,977
- Very precise.
- He's smart.

296
00:08:50,977 --> 00:08:53,177
All commentaries are delivered out of experience.

297
00:08:53,177 --> 00:08:54,707
- That's why he's the chairman.
- That's right.

298
00:08:54,847 --> 00:08:56,217
- I didn't realize that.
- Experience.

299
00:08:56,217 --> 00:08:58,717
- That's not a precise comparison.
- You can't explain without it.

300
00:08:58,987 --> 00:09:00,717
- That's not exactly the case.
- Hee Chul is right.

301
00:09:00,717 --> 00:09:04,287
I'm both the sportscaster and the commentator on that show.

302
00:09:04,287 --> 00:09:05,727
Because the others have no experience.

303
00:09:05,727 --> 00:09:07,227
- Okay. I understand now.
- He fulfills all requirements.

304
00:09:07,227 --> 00:09:09,327
Yoon Gy, is this your first time being a commentator?

305
00:09:09,327 --> 00:09:10,597
This is my first time.

306
00:09:11,057 --> 00:09:12,597
So I'm very nervous.

307
00:09:12,597 --> 00:09:14,497
I commentated...

308
00:09:14,497 --> 00:09:16,367
- for the Sochi Winter Games.
- Yes, you did.

309
00:09:16,537 --> 00:09:17,697
- The Sochi Winter Games?
- He commentated on speed skating.

310
00:09:17,697 --> 00:09:19,737
- I did it because... So I saw...
- So...

311
00:09:19,737 --> 00:09:21,307
Lee Sang Hwa win the gold medal.

312
00:09:21,307 --> 00:09:23,037
- Since it was a live broadcast, - So I...

313
00:09:23,037 --> 00:09:25,977
he only shouted during the games to avoid making mistakes.

314
00:09:25,977 --> 00:09:27,307
- I only said some filler words.
- Right.

315
00:09:27,307 --> 00:09:29,517
I remember how Ho Dong commentated on that game.

316
00:09:29,517 --> 00:09:31,917
- It was 12 years from now.
- That's right.

317
00:09:31,917 --> 00:09:35,247
He commentated on the game where Lee Sang Hwa won the gold medal.

318
00:09:35,557 --> 00:09:38,357
How should I put it? He commentated on the game...

319
00:09:38,357 --> 00:09:40,327
as a former athlete, not as an entertainer.

320
00:09:40,327 --> 00:09:42,397
- And that was really cool.
- But that disappointed many people.

321
00:09:42,397 --> 00:09:45,567
- They expected a fun commentary.
- Because he's an entertainer now.

322
00:09:45,727 --> 00:09:47,597
- I see. I guess he was too serious.
- They expected something different.

323
00:09:47,597 --> 00:09:48,737
People said he should never have done it...

324
00:09:48,737 --> 00:09:49,867
- if he was going to do it that way.
- Exactly.

325
00:09:49,867 --> 00:09:51,097
He was hired because he was expected to be funny.

326
00:09:51,097 --> 00:09:52,737
- But for Winter Games...
- Why did they hire a TV celebrity?

327
00:09:52,737 --> 00:09:54,337
- They hired him to make it fun.
- You shouldn't try to be funny...

328
00:09:54,337 --> 00:09:55,937
when it comes to Winter Games.

329
00:09:55,937 --> 00:09:57,377
- But back then...
- Then Ho Dong,

330
00:09:57,377 --> 00:09:59,507
- Imagine the tension.
- you should've refused to do it.

331
00:09:59,507 --> 00:10:01,177
- Why did you even do it?
- I refused at first.

332
00:10:01,177 --> 00:10:02,577
- You should've made it fun.
- Right.

333
00:10:02,577 --> 00:10:04,417
- You should've made it fun.
- You should know better than that.

334
00:10:04,417 --> 00:10:05,517
I'll see how well you commentate.

335
00:10:06,687 --> 00:10:08,987
- Yoon Gy will be too pressured.
- I'll see how well you do, Yoon Gy.

336
00:10:08,987 --> 00:10:10,117
- Seong Jae.
- Yoon Gy will overdo it.

337
00:10:10,117 --> 00:10:11,217
- I'll deliver a fun commentary.
- He'll overdo it.

338
00:10:11,217 --> 00:10:14,327
Seong Jae, how well do you expect Korea will do in the Winter Games?

339
00:10:14,387 --> 00:10:15,527
How well will Korea do?

340
00:10:15,527 --> 00:10:18,497
- Korea is very good at short track.
- They will win some medals.

341
00:10:18,497 --> 00:10:19,667
- So we need them...
- To win some medals.

342
00:10:19,667 --> 00:10:22,097
to win many gold medals so that Korea's ranking goes up.

343
00:10:22,097 --> 00:10:23,097
That's right.

344
00:10:23,467 --> 00:10:26,667
- I expect four gold medals.
- Four gold medals?

345
00:10:26,667 --> 00:10:29,707
- Four or more would be great.
- That would be really great.

346
00:10:29,707 --> 00:10:31,277
- That would be so great.
- I hope so too.

347
00:10:31,407 --> 00:10:32,847
How many gold medals can be won...

348
00:10:32,847 --> 00:10:34,247
- in short track speed skating?
- In short track speed skating...

349
00:10:34,447 --> 00:10:36,117
- Nine gold medals can be won.
- How many events are there?

350
00:10:36,117 --> 00:10:37,377
- How many events...
- Nine.

351
00:10:37,377 --> 00:10:39,587
There are 2 in the 500m, 1,000m, 1,500m.

352
00:10:39,887 --> 00:10:41,287
- And relays.
- Also 3,000m and 5,000m.

353
00:10:41,317 --> 00:10:43,187
- And a mixed team relay.
- And one in a mixed team relay.

354
00:10:43,187 --> 00:10:46,127
I thought you were talking about the amount of your debt left to pay.

355
00:10:47,357 --> 00:10:48,527
You went on, "3,000 and 5,000..."

356
00:10:48,527 --> 00:10:51,057
- I thought he borrowed more money.
- It went down a lot.

357
00:10:51,057 --> 00:10:52,467
- That makes sense.
- He said, "3,000 and 5,000..."

358
00:10:52,467 --> 00:10:54,527
Also... Although I won't commentate on the event,

359
00:10:54,527 --> 00:10:56,797
- in snowboarding, - Right.

360
00:10:56,797 --> 00:10:59,007
- Korea will likely win some medals.
- That's right.

361
00:10:59,137 --> 00:11:02,807
Not many Koreans know this, but there are snowboarding events...

362
00:11:02,807 --> 00:11:03,837
- Halfpipe.
- like halfpipe...

363
00:11:03,837 --> 00:11:06,277
Korean athletes who will participate in those events...

364
00:11:06,407 --> 00:11:09,817
- are expected to win a gold medal.
- Right.

365
00:11:09,817 --> 00:11:13,117
- That's great.
- There are great snowboarders.

366
00:11:13,287 --> 00:11:15,757
There are 1 man and 1 woman, who are both teenagers.

367
00:11:15,757 --> 00:11:17,387
- They're very young.
- Yes.

368
00:11:17,457 --> 00:11:20,287
I watched the halfpipe games in the world championship recently.

369
00:11:20,457 --> 00:11:22,997
- I watched Lee Chae Un's games.
- Right.

370
00:11:22,997 --> 00:11:24,297
He performed really well.

371
00:11:24,297 --> 00:11:25,827
And it felt as if the other players...

372
00:11:25,997 --> 00:11:27,267
had already given up on defeating him...

373
00:11:27,697 --> 00:11:29,997
because they knew he'd do well. That was the atmosphere there.

374
00:11:30,197 --> 00:11:31,737
- That's cool.
- It made me...

375
00:11:31,737 --> 00:11:33,307
expect him to win a medal.

376
00:11:33,507 --> 00:11:36,977
If he wins a gold medal in halfpipe, he'll be the first.

377
00:11:37,237 --> 00:11:38,507
- Really?
- The first Korean to do so.

378
00:11:39,077 --> 00:11:41,107
- It's an incredible achievement.
- Indeed.

379
00:11:41,107 --> 00:11:43,217
- Curling also draws attention too.
- That's right.

380
00:11:43,217 --> 00:11:44,517
- As for curling...
- Is Korea a major contender?

381
00:11:44,677 --> 00:11:45,887
You should consider the team as a major contender.

382
00:11:45,887 --> 00:11:48,957
Korea is good at target sports like archery and curling.

383
00:11:49,217 --> 00:11:51,057
- Right.
- Korea is good at target sports.

384
00:11:51,057 --> 00:11:52,487
(The national team players to play in women's events and mixed double)

385
00:11:52,487 --> 00:11:53,657
We'll have to wait and see how it goes,

386
00:11:53,657 --> 00:11:55,827
- but if they win 1 or 2 medals, - They'll be in the top 3?

387
00:11:56,197 --> 00:11:57,257
- it will help Team Korea...
- They'll do well.

388
00:11:57,257 --> 00:11:59,967
- We'll find out about them 1 by 1.
- I hope so.

389
00:12:00,267 --> 00:12:03,137
First up is Seong Jae. He wrote, "veteran sportscaster."

390
00:12:03,267 --> 00:12:06,137
- Well, we have to admit that.
- His family name is Bae.

391
00:12:06,137 --> 00:12:09,307
- He joined SBS as an announcer...
- That's right.

392
00:12:09,307 --> 00:12:10,707
- to start his career.
- Yes.

393
00:12:10,807 --> 00:12:13,777
But I saw him wearing a headset more than him hosting a news show.

394
00:12:14,007 --> 00:12:15,477
That image comes in my head first.

395
00:12:15,477 --> 00:12:17,477
I've been mostly working as a sportscaster.

396
00:12:17,477 --> 00:12:18,777
I rarely do a variety show.

397
00:12:18,777 --> 00:12:19,887
I mostly commentate on sports games or host a radio show.

398
00:12:19,887 --> 00:12:21,517
- So I always wear a headset.
- Right.

399
00:12:21,517 --> 00:12:24,057
Seong Jae, how long have you been working as a sportscaster?

400
00:12:24,117 --> 00:12:25,687
I've been doing it since 2008,

401
00:12:25,687 --> 00:12:27,527
- so this year is the 19th year.
- It's been almost 19 years.

402
00:12:28,187 --> 00:12:30,227
But Seong Jae, you didn't join SBS...

403
00:12:30,227 --> 00:12:32,397
- as a sportscaster.
- That's right.

404
00:12:32,397 --> 00:12:33,767
You joined SBS as an announcer.

405
00:12:33,767 --> 00:12:36,097
Did someone recommend the job or did you want to do it?

406
00:12:36,267 --> 00:12:37,667
I became an announcer...

407
00:12:37,667 --> 00:12:39,637
without any plans or preparation.

408
00:12:39,637 --> 00:12:42,007
I took the exam in my senior year in college, and I passed it.

409
00:12:42,007 --> 00:12:44,977
After that, I had to decide what to do as an announcer.

410
00:12:44,977 --> 00:12:46,947
Back then, it was called the announcer-tainer era.

411
00:12:46,947 --> 00:12:49,347
- The announcer-tainer era.
- Many announcers did variety shows.

412
00:12:49,417 --> 00:12:51,817
But I didn't think variety shows suited me...

413
00:12:51,877 --> 00:12:53,717
because I wasn't funny.

414
00:12:54,217 --> 00:12:57,957
Since I had been a huge fan of sports since I was little,

415
00:12:58,157 --> 00:12:59,387
I thought I could be a sportscaster.

416
00:12:59,387 --> 00:13:02,857
Back then, only senior announcers commentated for sports events.

417
00:13:03,197 --> 00:13:07,067
But SBS gave me an opportunity even though I was a rookie.

418
00:13:07,067 --> 00:13:09,137
So I tried it, and the result was good.

419
00:13:09,137 --> 00:13:10,737
- I've been doing it ever since.
- You continued doing it.

420
00:13:10,837 --> 00:13:12,507
So the network offered you the opportunity first?

421
00:13:12,507 --> 00:13:15,737
Yes. They selected sportscasters among the SBS announcers...

422
00:13:15,737 --> 00:13:18,737
through auditions for two years.

423
00:13:18,737 --> 00:13:21,277
- You competed in an audition?
- Yes.

424
00:13:21,447 --> 00:13:23,747
If you've been a sportscaster for 19 years,

425
00:13:24,017 --> 00:13:25,787
how many times did you participate in Summer and Winter Games?

426
00:13:26,217 --> 00:13:27,487
- "Participate?"
- No, I mean...

427
00:13:27,487 --> 00:13:28,887
- He meant, "commentate."
- Right, "commentate."

428
00:13:28,957 --> 00:13:31,287
- That's an athlete's point of view.
- Right.

429
00:13:31,557 --> 00:13:34,627
This is my 5th time in Winter Games, and I did 5 times in Summer Games.

430
00:13:34,787 --> 00:13:35,897
So ten times in total.

431
00:13:35,897 --> 00:13:37,127
(He has commentated for Summer and Winter Games 10 times.)

432
00:13:37,127 --> 00:13:39,467
- It's held every two years.
- He has a lot of experience.

433
00:13:39,767 --> 00:13:41,297
- How many times did you go?
- He's already a living legend.

434
00:13:41,497 --> 00:13:43,897
- Let's not talk about that.
- I'll do it for another 20 years.

435
00:13:43,897 --> 00:13:45,867
- There's the World Cup too.
- That's right.

436
00:13:45,867 --> 00:13:46,967
And the Asian Games too.

437
00:13:46,967 --> 00:13:49,537
- When you commentate on a game, - He's the king of sports.

438
00:13:49,537 --> 00:13:51,937
- you watch it in person.
- That's right.

439
00:13:52,247 --> 00:13:55,347
I think there are many good things about being a sportscaster.

440
00:13:55,477 --> 00:13:58,147
- The network sends me there.
- That's right.

441
00:13:58,147 --> 00:14:00,447
- You can watch it in person.
- Yes. I'm supposed to pay for it.

442
00:14:00,547 --> 00:14:02,717
But I get paid, and I get to watch it...

443
00:14:02,717 --> 00:14:03,917
- in the best spot.
- That's a great benefit.

444
00:14:03,917 --> 00:14:05,157
I shout and cheer while commentating on the game.

445
00:14:05,157 --> 00:14:06,257
- I practically have fun.
- Right.

446
00:14:06,587 --> 00:14:07,887
You do your work and make money from it.

447
00:14:07,887 --> 00:14:09,397
- You get a good spot too.
- Ho Dong wanted that too, but...

448
00:14:09,397 --> 00:14:12,097
(Shouting, screaming, and exclaiming)

449
00:14:12,867 --> 00:14:14,167
All he did was shout.

450
00:14:14,467 --> 00:14:16,397
- But I saw Ho Dong...
- Shouldn't Ho Dong...

451
00:14:16,397 --> 00:14:17,967
- crying while watching the game.
- give back the money?

452
00:14:17,967 --> 00:14:19,037
- Did he cry?
- Yes.

453
00:14:19,037 --> 00:14:21,467
Seong Jae was touched by my sincerity.

454
00:14:21,767 --> 00:14:23,907
- He had to do something.
- Right. He had to do something.

455
00:14:23,907 --> 00:14:25,477
He had already been paid, but he was like...

456
00:14:26,407 --> 00:14:27,947
"Oh, goodness. What do I do?"

457
00:14:28,007 --> 00:14:30,147
(Crying)

458
00:14:30,147 --> 00:14:32,787
- He cried because he was worried.
- Exactly.

459
00:14:32,787 --> 00:14:34,217
- He thought he was in trouble.
- The game ended.

460
00:14:34,217 --> 00:14:37,217
The 500m event ends in a blink of an eye.

461
00:14:37,457 --> 00:14:38,517
- That's true.
- Right.

462
00:14:38,517 --> 00:14:40,387
It feels as if it ended within three seconds.

463
00:14:40,387 --> 00:14:42,757
- It ends within 45 seconds.
- It's a little over 30 seconds.

464
00:14:42,757 --> 00:14:45,897
I was afraid I might disturb the players.

465
00:14:45,997 --> 00:14:47,467
So I had to be very careful.

466
00:14:47,467 --> 00:14:49,197
But before the game, I talked a lot.

467
00:14:49,197 --> 00:14:51,667
- Also, Ho Dong...
- I see. It ended very quickly.

468
00:14:51,667 --> 00:14:53,937
is always careful doing everything.

469
00:14:54,007 --> 00:14:56,377
- I guess he was extra careful.
- But still...

470
00:14:56,377 --> 00:14:57,737
"One, two! Keep going!"

471
00:14:57,737 --> 00:14:59,177
- You could've cheered for them.
- Right. He could've done it.

472
00:14:59,177 --> 00:15:01,347
- "Go, Lee Sang Hwa! One, two!"
- Exactly.

473
00:15:01,347 --> 00:15:03,547
Baby Sang Hwa, doo, doo, doo, doo

474
00:15:04,417 --> 00:15:06,787
- "Run! Go!" You could've done it.
- But hey...

475
00:15:06,917 --> 00:15:08,647
- The viewers must've laughed.
- You think...

476
00:15:08,647 --> 00:15:10,717
- You think you could do that...
- That's why you were hired.

477
00:15:10,717 --> 00:15:12,557
- in a final match of Winter Games?
- Of course. You should've done it.

478
00:15:12,557 --> 00:15:13,987
Really? Then show me how you do it.

479
00:15:13,987 --> 00:15:15,187
- I didn't get any opportunities.
- Right.

480
00:15:15,187 --> 00:15:17,297
- I can commentate on a soccer game.
- You were hired to do it.

481
00:15:17,397 --> 00:15:19,097
- No, that's not true.
- "One, two!"

482
00:15:19,097 --> 00:15:20,627
- At least sing "Baby Sang Hwa."
- "Baby Sang Hwa."

483
00:15:20,697 --> 00:15:24,337
- The athletes waited four years...
- Baby Sang Hwa, doo, doo, doo, doo

484
00:15:24,767 --> 00:15:26,107
for the moment of the final match.

485
00:15:26,107 --> 00:15:28,007
You can't even imagine the weight of seriousness.

486
00:15:28,207 --> 00:15:30,407
You wouldn't dare speak in that moment.

487
00:15:31,207 --> 00:15:36,877
(He felt the weight of time spent and was careful about what he said.)

488
00:15:36,877 --> 00:15:38,917
How do you get paid?

489
00:15:38,917 --> 00:15:40,547
For the whole project or per event?

490
00:15:40,887 --> 00:15:42,987
- Oh, I'm curious about that.
- I'm curious about it too.

491
00:15:42,987 --> 00:15:45,257
- I'm curious.
- I went freelance recently.

492
00:15:45,257 --> 00:15:46,657
- You were an employee.
- Before that, it was included...

493
00:15:46,657 --> 00:15:48,087
in my monthly salary.

494
00:15:48,087 --> 00:15:50,557
As a freelancer, I get paid for a whole competition.

495
00:15:50,997 --> 00:15:52,427
- Oh, I see.
- Not per event.

496
00:15:52,427 --> 00:15:54,467
- You sign for a whole competition?
- Yes.

497
00:15:54,467 --> 00:15:56,867
- So they work me to the bone.
- You earn about 500,000 dollars?

498
00:15:57,297 --> 00:15:58,297
- What did you say?
- Are you paid 500,000 dollars?

499
00:15:58,297 --> 00:16:00,867
- No.
- Seong Jae, you are...

500
00:16:01,267 --> 00:16:03,277
the main sportscaster at this Winter Games.

501
00:16:03,707 --> 00:16:06,507
How many events do you commentate on?

502
00:16:07,077 --> 00:16:08,847
It's similar to the past Winter Games.

503
00:16:08,847 --> 00:16:10,617
I host the opening and closing ceremonies.

504
00:16:10,877 --> 00:16:12,547
And I commentate on short track and speed skating.

505
00:16:12,787 --> 00:16:14,947
I can't commentate on many events.

506
00:16:14,947 --> 00:16:17,517
There are so many games in short track and speed skating.

507
00:16:17,517 --> 00:16:19,287
- I can't do anything else.
- Really? Why?

508
00:16:19,487 --> 00:16:20,557
Yoon Gy, why are you surprised?

509
00:16:20,557 --> 00:16:22,757
Short track and speed skating games...

510
00:16:22,897 --> 00:16:25,327
- are held every other day.
- If they overlap?

511
00:16:25,697 --> 00:16:26,767
That means you work every day.

512
00:16:26,767 --> 00:16:28,767
- Yes. I have to.
- Every day?

513
00:16:28,767 --> 00:16:30,137
- You work every day.
- Only I work every day.

514
00:16:30,237 --> 00:16:32,507
You've been working your tail off since you went freelance.

515
00:16:32,507 --> 00:16:33,867
- Yes. They work me to the bone.
- To make money you couldn't earn...

516
00:16:35,367 --> 00:16:36,977
- I practically get locked up.
- No wonder why...

517
00:16:36,977 --> 00:16:38,977
everyone at SM Culture and Contents came here earlier.

518
00:16:39,447 --> 00:16:41,747
I saw them all here.

519
00:16:41,747 --> 00:16:43,677
- Surprised, I said hello to them.
- That's not the case.

520
00:16:43,677 --> 00:16:46,387
- He came here to make more money.
- Winter Games and World Cup...

521
00:16:46,387 --> 00:16:48,647
For Seong Jae, these sports events...

522
00:16:48,747 --> 00:16:50,357
are huge opportunities, not adversity.

523
00:16:50,357 --> 00:16:52,317
- Jang Hoon is right.
- It's a huge opportunity for him.

524
00:16:52,317 --> 00:16:54,957
What's the hardest sport to commentate on?

525
00:16:54,957 --> 00:16:56,897
- The hardest sports are...
- I think short track is hard.

526
00:16:56,897 --> 00:16:58,227
- Right.
- soccer and short track.

527
00:16:58,227 --> 00:16:59,967
- I think it's difficult.
- Short track is difficult.

528
00:16:59,967 --> 00:17:02,667
When the viewers find the rules of a sport tricky,

529
00:17:02,897 --> 00:17:04,237
it's easy for us to commentate on it.

530
00:17:04,237 --> 00:17:06,207
We just have to explain the rules for most of the time.

531
00:17:06,367 --> 00:17:09,377
But in soccer, for example,

532
00:17:09,537 --> 00:17:10,707
players fight for the ball...

533
00:17:10,837 --> 00:17:12,707
- without many clear rules.
- Right.

534
00:17:12,707 --> 00:17:13,977
- What matters is making a goal.
- Yes.

535
00:17:13,977 --> 00:17:16,317
That's why explaining the tactics isn't easy.

536
00:17:16,477 --> 00:17:19,417
In short-track speed skating, the disqualifications are unclear.

537
00:17:19,417 --> 00:17:21,017
- Totally.
- Explaining the reason...

538
00:17:21,017 --> 00:17:22,347
- True.
- for disqualification is tough.

539
00:17:22,347 --> 00:17:23,757
- Right.
- There should be...

540
00:17:23,757 --> 00:17:25,387
clear criteria.

541
00:17:25,657 --> 00:17:27,287
But at times, the player who arrives first...

542
00:17:27,287 --> 00:17:28,687
- gets disqualified.
- Yes.

543
00:17:28,687 --> 00:17:30,697
- Exactly.
- It's really...

544
00:17:30,697 --> 00:17:32,867
Now, it's easier to tell the reason.

545
00:17:32,867 --> 00:17:35,597
In the past, a certain amount of hustle was allowed.

546
00:17:35,597 --> 00:17:39,267
But now, the player who starts the hustle gets disqualified.

547
00:17:39,937 --> 00:17:40,937
- Then...
- Yes?

548
00:17:40,937 --> 00:17:42,337
the hustle at the start might get worse.

549
00:17:42,337 --> 00:17:44,407
- The start hustle...
- The players must make way.

550
00:17:44,407 --> 00:17:46,307
- Really?
- The faster player must push ahead.

551
00:17:46,307 --> 00:17:48,307
- Yes.
- There will barely be any hustles.

552
00:17:48,307 --> 00:17:49,747
Try a hustle, and that player...

553
00:17:49,747 --> 00:17:51,377
- Right.
- will be monitored again.

554
00:17:51,377 --> 00:17:54,617
What about golden sayings? You know, like famous quotations.

555
00:17:54,617 --> 00:17:58,157
No, I'm the type who refrains from using golden sayings.

556
00:17:58,157 --> 00:18:00,627
Once I start saying famous quotations,

557
00:18:00,627 --> 00:18:02,227
- Yes?
- people expect more.

558
00:18:02,357 --> 00:18:05,097
That won't help my career last long.

559
00:18:05,297 --> 00:18:06,997
Does Seong Jae not have any famous sayings?

560
00:18:06,997 --> 00:18:09,367
- Among the ones by Seong Jae...
- Tell us some.

561
00:18:09,367 --> 00:18:10,837
- that I've heard, - Yes?

562
00:18:10,837 --> 00:18:13,437
isn't the Germany karaoke saying famous?

563
00:18:13,437 --> 00:18:14,707
Did you go to karaoke in Germany?

564
00:18:14,707 --> 00:18:17,037
No. During the Russia World Cup,

565
00:18:17,037 --> 00:18:18,437
we were up against Germany...

566
00:18:18,437 --> 00:18:20,447
and won, which was called the Miracle of Kazan.

567
00:18:20,447 --> 00:18:21,477
- Right.
- Yes.

568
00:18:21,477 --> 00:18:24,017
The game was about to end 1-0,

569
00:18:24,017 --> 00:18:27,047
but about five minutes of additional time were added.

570
00:18:27,487 --> 00:18:29,987
"What's going on? Are we at a karaoke?" was what I said.

571
00:18:29,987 --> 00:18:31,557
- Because of the additional time?
- I get it.

572
00:18:31,787 --> 00:18:33,657
- The extra time.
- The additional time?

573
00:18:33,657 --> 00:18:35,427
Additional time was added out of the blue.

574
00:18:35,427 --> 00:18:37,257
- That's a famous saying.
- Adding time on top...

575
00:18:37,257 --> 00:18:38,657
of an existing one got me upset.

576
00:18:38,727 --> 00:18:40,667
Wasn't there another one during the match with Sweden?

577
00:18:40,667 --> 00:18:43,397
We also had a match with Sweden back then.

578
00:18:43,397 --> 00:18:45,837
Sweden was winning 1-0, but the Swedish players...

579
00:18:45,837 --> 00:18:47,937
- wouldn't get up.
- The so-called bed soccer.

580
00:18:47,937 --> 00:18:49,007
They were playing bed soccer.

581
00:18:49,177 --> 00:18:51,707
As Sweden is known for their furniture brand,

582
00:18:51,707 --> 00:18:55,007
I said, "Is this a commercial for IKEA or what?"

583
00:18:55,007 --> 00:18:56,777
Are you allowed to make comments like that?

584
00:18:56,777 --> 00:18:58,177
- I just...
- He does it.

585
00:18:58,177 --> 00:18:59,987
Seong Jae hits the spot...

586
00:18:59,987 --> 00:19:01,147
- of the viewers.
- Exactly.

587
00:19:01,147 --> 00:19:03,357
- He's a pro at knowing what to say.
- Yes.

588
00:19:03,457 --> 00:19:06,387
Here's what I want to know. I don't know much about soccer.

589
00:19:06,527 --> 00:19:09,087
But when I watch the games, the sportscaster knows...

590
00:19:09,087 --> 00:19:10,997
- the names of all players.
- I know, right?

591
00:19:10,997 --> 00:19:12,767
At times, they even say the last name.

592
00:19:12,767 --> 00:19:15,197
- Do you study their names?
- There must be long names too.

593
00:19:15,427 --> 00:19:18,767
Sportscasters don't only cover the World Cup.

594
00:19:18,767 --> 00:19:21,167
Normally, players who are considered good in famous leagues,

595
00:19:21,167 --> 00:19:24,177
like the European leagues, take part in the World Cup.

596
00:19:24,407 --> 00:19:26,777
To sportscasters covering the leagues, they know the players.

597
00:19:26,977 --> 00:19:28,607
The toughest moment would be...

598
00:19:28,607 --> 00:19:30,277
- the preliminaries held in Asia.
- I see.

599
00:19:30,747 --> 00:19:32,447
There are players we're not familiar with.

600
00:19:32,447 --> 00:19:34,547
- Of course.
- For example, Vietnamese players...

601
00:19:34,547 --> 00:19:36,017
or Thai players.

602
00:19:36,057 --> 00:19:37,857
Seong Jae had posted something on social media.

603
00:19:37,857 --> 00:19:38,857
Can you zoom in on it?

604
00:19:38,857 --> 00:19:41,457
He has to mention the names of the players passing the ball.

605
00:19:41,457 --> 00:19:43,827
Do you have all the names in your head, Seong Jae?

606
00:19:44,027 --> 00:19:46,127
Yes, I memorized the names of the starters.

607
00:19:46,127 --> 00:19:47,167
- Really?
- Yes.

608
00:19:47,167 --> 00:19:48,697
But all of them have uniform numbers.

609
00:19:48,697 --> 00:19:50,297
- The names are...
- Seong Jae,

610
00:19:50,297 --> 00:19:52,137
read the names as if you're covering a game.

611
00:19:52,137 --> 00:19:53,137
Where? I can't even read any.

612
00:19:53,137 --> 00:19:54,207
- Hey.
- The pronunciations are hard.

613
00:19:54,207 --> 00:19:55,607
Korea is playing against Laos right now.

614
00:19:55,607 --> 00:19:57,707
- Laos?
- Come on, let's watch it.

615
00:19:57,707 --> 00:19:59,547
- Turn on the TV. It's on.
- The game is on.

616
00:19:59,647 --> 00:20:02,277
(World Cup Asia Preliminary, Korea versus Laos)

617
00:20:02,477 --> 00:20:03,777
Here's Laos' starting lineup.

618
00:20:03,777 --> 00:20:05,617
Phoutpasong Sengdalavong, Sengphachan Bounthisanh,

619
00:20:05,617 --> 00:20:07,317
Vanhasith Thilavongsa, Khamla Pinkeo,

620
00:20:07,317 --> 00:20:09,317
Khamphoumy Hanevilay, Moukda Souksavath,

621
00:20:09,317 --> 00:20:11,057
Oudomsith Singla, Phoumai Souvandee,

622
00:20:11,057 --> 00:20:12,417
Saynakhonevieng Phommapanya,

623
00:20:12,417 --> 00:20:13,487
Thotnilath Sibounhuang,

624
00:20:13,487 --> 00:20:15,157
- Keoviengphet Liththideth, - Gosh.

625
00:20:15,157 --> 00:20:17,057
Khonsavanh Sihavong, Manolom Phomsouvanh,

626
00:20:17,057 --> 00:20:18,257
- Paseuthsack Souliyavong, - Goodness.

627
00:20:18,257 --> 00:20:19,967
Phouthone Innalay, Phoutthasay Khochalern,

628
00:20:19,967 --> 00:20:21,767
Souksakhone Bountathip, Tiny Bounmalay,

629
00:20:21,767 --> 00:20:23,837
Chanthaphone Waenvongsoth,

630
00:20:23,837 --> 00:20:25,597
Khampheng Sayavutthi, Sitthideth Khanthavong,

631
00:20:25,597 --> 00:20:27,267
Souk Aphone Vongchiengkham,

632
00:20:27,267 --> 00:20:30,637
and Soukchinda Natphasouk.

633
00:20:32,077 --> 00:20:34,647
- To actually read that?
- Amazing.

634
00:20:34,777 --> 00:20:37,777
(A stunt-like lineup announcement)

635
00:20:38,017 --> 00:20:39,517
- It was like a debate.
- Gosh.

636
00:20:39,517 --> 00:20:41,217
- That was incredible.
- Try it, Yoon Gy.

637
00:20:41,347 --> 00:20:42,787
- Go ahead.
- It's not easy.

638
00:20:42,787 --> 00:20:44,057
Ready? You must say it fast.

639
00:20:44,287 --> 00:20:45,787
Set, go.

640
00:20:46,327 --> 00:20:47,787
Phoutpasong Sanglangdavong,

641
00:20:47,787 --> 00:20:49,797
Sengphipang Bounthisanh,

642
00:20:49,997 --> 00:20:51,727
- Vanhasith Thilavongsa, - It's tough.

643
00:20:51,727 --> 00:20:52,927
- None is right.
- Khamla Pinkeo,

644
00:20:52,927 --> 00:20:54,227
- Khamphoumy...
- Enough.

645
00:20:54,297 --> 00:20:55,297
- Stop.
- Thank you to everyone...

646
00:20:55,297 --> 00:20:56,297
who has tuned in.

647
00:20:56,297 --> 00:20:57,937
- Bye.
- It's hard.

648
00:20:57,937 --> 00:20:59,507
- It ended while reading the names.
- Listen.

649
00:20:59,507 --> 00:21:00,837
You know, Lee Soo Geun?

650
00:21:00,837 --> 00:21:02,467
- The comedian.
- The comedian?

651
00:21:02,467 --> 00:21:03,507
He's one of the guest commentators.

652
00:21:03,507 --> 00:21:04,837
Here's Laos' starting lineup.

653
00:21:04,837 --> 00:21:06,677
Phoutpasong Sengdalavong, Sengphachan Bounthisanh,

654
00:21:06,677 --> 00:21:08,747
Vanhasith Thilavongsa, Khamla Pinkeo,

655
00:21:08,747 --> 00:21:10,017
Khamphoumy Hanevilay,

656
00:21:10,017 --> 00:21:11,217
Moukda Souksavath,

657
00:21:11,217 --> 00:21:12,547
and the coach is Cha Bum Kun.

658
00:21:12,817 --> 00:21:14,317
- Cha Bum Kun?
- Hold on.

659
00:21:14,787 --> 00:21:16,617
- The names...
- Are you just pushing ahead?

660
00:21:16,617 --> 00:21:18,357
- That was him...
- Yes.

661
00:21:18,357 --> 00:21:21,787
just now reading off the list. The problem is...

662
00:21:21,787 --> 00:21:22,957
During passes, right?

663
00:21:22,957 --> 00:21:24,797
- True.
- when the players...

664
00:21:24,797 --> 00:21:26,527
- pass the ball...
- The names must be said instantly.

665
00:21:26,527 --> 00:21:28,497
or when there's a foul. He has to have the name memorized.

666
00:21:28,497 --> 00:21:29,497
- Exactly.
- That's the tough part.

667
00:21:29,497 --> 00:21:31,197
Did you ever make a mistake?

668
00:21:31,337 --> 00:21:33,237
Even if I make a mistake with names,

669
00:21:33,237 --> 00:21:35,837
- the viewers don't catch it.
- We wouldn't.

670
00:21:36,007 --> 00:21:37,477
Did you ever get a Korean player's name mixed up?

671
00:21:37,477 --> 00:21:39,077
I sometimes did get them mixed up.

672
00:21:39,077 --> 00:21:40,777
When the players are running around...

673
00:21:40,777 --> 00:21:41,807
- You can't catch them right away.
- No.

674
00:21:41,807 --> 00:21:43,677
- I miss the uniform number.
- Right.

675
00:21:43,677 --> 00:21:46,247
It doesn't matter much when the ball is being passed.

676
00:21:46,417 --> 00:21:49,557
But it'd be bad if I mixed up the names at an eventful moment,

677
00:21:49,557 --> 00:21:51,857
- like when a goal has been scored.
- Exactly.

678
00:21:51,987 --> 00:21:53,287
- Then...
- Mistaking the player who scored?

679
00:21:53,287 --> 00:21:55,527
- The timing...
- Here's what I heard.

680
00:21:55,527 --> 00:21:59,127
Some uniforms shine and are easy to read.

681
00:21:59,127 --> 00:22:00,397
Totally.

682
00:22:00,497 --> 00:22:03,737
But the numbers on some uniforms are similar in color,

683
00:22:03,737 --> 00:22:06,807
- Exactly.
- making it hard to read.

684
00:22:06,807 --> 00:22:08,207
Like is it an 8 or a 9?

685
00:22:08,207 --> 00:22:10,507
- The sports legend gets it.
- Yes.

686
00:22:10,807 --> 00:22:11,937
Weirdly enough,

687
00:22:11,937 --> 00:22:13,077
- Right.
- current sports uniforms...

688
00:22:13,077 --> 00:22:15,677
are focused on design and less on distinguishing players.

689
00:22:16,077 --> 00:22:17,777
The font of the numbers changes.

690
00:22:17,977 --> 00:22:20,547
The numbers are hard to tell...

691
00:22:20,547 --> 00:22:23,157
if the uniform is red while the number is black.

692
00:22:23,157 --> 00:22:24,717
- If it's dark.
- In the past, it was white.

693
00:22:24,987 --> 00:22:27,527
Are there times when you burst into laughter mid-coverage?

694
00:22:27,827 --> 00:22:29,227
- Did you ever make a blunder?
- We had...

695
00:22:29,227 --> 00:22:30,757
a player named Kim Shin Wook.

696
00:22:30,757 --> 00:22:32,127
- He was super tall.
- I remember.

697
00:22:32,127 --> 00:22:33,367
- During the Incheon Game.
- Yes.

698
00:22:33,367 --> 00:22:36,767
Kim Shin Wook had an aerial duel with the opposing team's goalkeeper.

699
00:22:37,237 --> 00:22:38,997
Just when he was about to score with a header,

700
00:22:38,997 --> 00:22:40,767
the goalkeeper had already caught the ball.

701
00:22:41,067 --> 00:22:43,077
But as Kim Shin Wook is a big player,

702
00:22:43,077 --> 00:22:45,177
- the goalkeeper was pushed...
- Together?

703
00:22:45,177 --> 00:22:47,277
into the goalpost with the ball.

704
00:22:47,547 --> 00:22:49,007
It was so funny back then that I couldn't...

705
00:22:49,007 --> 00:22:50,577
- continue.
- Is that considered a goal?

706
00:22:50,577 --> 00:22:51,647
- What?
- It's a foul play.

707
00:22:51,647 --> 00:22:54,287
- A foul play.
- Was your laughter broadcast?

708
00:22:54,287 --> 00:22:55,887
I said, "Isn't it two goals,"

709
00:22:55,887 --> 00:22:58,387
"as he scored both the goalkeeper and the goal?" Before I knew it...

710
00:22:58,387 --> 00:22:59,757
It's fine to laugh if it's funny.

711
00:22:59,757 --> 00:23:00,987
- Totally.
- Yes.

712
00:23:00,987 --> 00:23:02,897
- People get it.
- Seong Jae knows when to laugh.

713
00:23:02,897 --> 00:23:05,257
In Europe, when a goal is scored, the commentator is like,

714
00:23:05,257 --> 00:23:06,627
- "Score!"
- South America.

715
00:23:06,627 --> 00:23:08,097
- It's no joke in South America.
- Is it South America?

716
00:23:08,097 --> 00:23:09,997
- Argentina and such.
- Spain too, right?

717
00:23:09,997 --> 00:23:11,267
South America, North and Central America.

718
00:23:11,267 --> 00:23:12,967
- Countries like Mexico.
- The energy is different.

719
00:23:12,967 --> 00:23:15,607
- Score!
- Score!

720
00:23:15,737 --> 00:23:17,707
- For real.
- Just like that.

721
00:23:17,837 --> 00:23:20,107
(Score! It's a score!)

722
00:23:20,847 --> 00:23:24,617
(The sportscaster has a larger lung capacity than the players.)

723
00:23:25,117 --> 00:23:27,017
- It lasts for a minute.
- For real, a minute.

724
00:23:27,017 --> 00:23:28,547
They say "score" for a minute.

725
00:23:28,547 --> 00:23:29,857
- True.
- Really?

726
00:23:29,857 --> 00:23:31,517
Score!

727
00:23:31,517 --> 00:23:34,657
How long they can shout is the South American sportscasters' pride.

728
00:23:34,657 --> 00:23:36,497
- Really?
- How long they can shout?

729
00:23:36,497 --> 00:23:37,497
Yes, the longer, the better.

730
00:23:37,497 --> 00:23:40,197
It's similar to "And it goes out."

731
00:23:40,527 --> 00:23:44,267
(And it's a score!)

732
00:23:45,637 --> 00:23:47,607
- Let's move on to Seung Hi.
- Next is Seung Hi.

733
00:23:47,607 --> 00:23:49,007
- Seung Hi wrote, - Gosh.

734
00:23:49,007 --> 00:23:50,907
"A talkative commentator."

735
00:23:50,907 --> 00:23:53,707
Correct. I love talking.

736
00:23:53,707 --> 00:23:56,617
Simply put, I love being a mood maker.

737
00:23:56,717 --> 00:23:58,747
That's why I talk more.

738
00:23:58,747 --> 00:24:01,147
Seung Hi repeats the same thing 2 to 3 times.

739
00:24:01,247 --> 00:24:02,447
If something happens,

740
00:24:02,447 --> 00:24:05,057
she's like, "Why? Why should I do it? Why?"

741
00:24:05,257 --> 00:24:07,327
"What are we doing today? What? And why?"

742
00:24:07,427 --> 00:24:08,687
She won't stop talking.

743
00:24:08,687 --> 00:24:12,427
I often spoke up for the players.

744
00:24:12,427 --> 00:24:13,967
You're like Kim Yeong Cheol.

745
00:24:14,867 --> 00:24:16,297
I say things 2 to 3 times.

746
00:24:16,937 --> 00:24:18,237
I'm not that bad.

747
00:24:19,137 --> 00:24:20,837
- She hates being compared.
- No.

748
00:24:20,837 --> 00:24:22,067
- You're not as bad as Yeong Cheol.
- But she likes talking.

749
00:24:22,067 --> 00:24:23,607
- I'm not that bad.
- You talk way too much.

750
00:24:23,607 --> 00:24:24,677
- You're not that bad?
- No.

751
00:24:24,677 --> 00:24:25,677
You talk too much.

752
00:24:25,677 --> 00:24:27,777
- When covering, it's better...
- Yes?

753
00:24:27,777 --> 00:24:29,077
- to talk more than less, right?
- Of course.

754
00:24:29,077 --> 00:24:30,077
- Yes.
- Totally.

755
00:24:30,077 --> 00:24:31,817
Doing the coverage with her was great.

756
00:24:31,817 --> 00:24:34,547
Most of the time, people remember...

757
00:24:34,547 --> 00:24:36,917
the legendary scenes of sports games.

758
00:24:36,917 --> 00:24:39,287
What the commentators shout...

759
00:24:39,287 --> 00:24:41,627
during those important moments is mostly memorable.

760
00:24:41,627 --> 00:24:44,157
But there are many boring moments too.

761
00:24:44,157 --> 00:24:46,827
The repeated boring moments lead to one eventful moment.

762
00:24:46,867 --> 00:24:49,197
Even during those boring moments, Seung Hi keeps talking.

763
00:24:49,197 --> 00:24:50,667
- She does, right?
- I can't stand...

764
00:24:50,667 --> 00:24:52,167
those silent moments.

765
00:24:52,167 --> 00:24:54,037
- So I talk.
- Here's what Seung Hi is good at.

766
00:24:54,037 --> 00:24:56,277
Seung Hi makes a guess of the next move,

767
00:24:56,277 --> 00:24:57,677
- and it actually happens.
- Exactly.

768
00:24:57,677 --> 00:24:59,337
Yes, I made many predictions.

769
00:24:59,337 --> 00:25:00,347
- Right?
- "The player should..."

770
00:25:00,347 --> 00:25:01,377
"Here they are!"

771
00:25:01,377 --> 00:25:02,647
- And it happens.
- Yes.

772
00:25:02,647 --> 00:25:04,117
Like an avatar blind date?

773
00:25:04,117 --> 00:25:06,647
Here's what I realized about great commentators.

774
00:25:06,647 --> 00:25:09,517
In sports, the situation keeps changing with time.

775
00:25:09,517 --> 00:25:11,357
The coverage should change too.

776
00:25:11,357 --> 00:25:13,027
But if the commentator doesn't move on...

777
00:25:13,027 --> 00:25:14,557
- and talks about the old scene...
- I get it.

778
00:25:14,557 --> 00:25:17,997
The scene has already changed.

779
00:25:18,197 --> 00:25:21,397
Knowing when to stop and move on is important.

780
00:25:21,397 --> 00:25:23,967
But to some commentators, it may be new.

781
00:25:23,967 --> 00:25:25,837
So they'd keep talking in the next scene.

782
00:25:25,837 --> 00:25:27,537
At times like that, Seong Jae cuts us off.

783
00:25:27,537 --> 00:25:29,637
- In the past, Seong Jae...
- He stops us.

784
00:25:29,637 --> 00:25:30,637
- He's a pro.
- Yes.

785
00:25:30,637 --> 00:25:32,877
Wasn't there a time when Seong Jae had to pull...

786
00:25:32,877 --> 00:25:34,877
a commentator down as he got too excited?

787
00:25:34,877 --> 00:25:36,877
- I remember.
- Wasn't it Jaegal Sung Yeol?

788
00:25:36,877 --> 00:25:38,277
- Yes, Jaegal Sung Yeol.
- As one...

789
00:25:38,277 --> 00:25:42,247
- of his juniors made a good record, - Yes?

790
00:25:42,447 --> 00:25:44,087
Jaegal Sung Yeol went out of frame.

791
00:25:44,087 --> 00:25:45,287
So I had to pull him down...

792
00:25:45,287 --> 00:25:46,887
- to his seat.
- Right?

793
00:25:46,887 --> 00:25:49,627
Seong Jae pulls the commentators back in.

794
00:25:49,897 --> 00:25:51,997
In the Olympics' broadcasting booth, we have a webcam.

795
00:25:51,997 --> 00:25:53,127
- There's a camera...
- You can see us...

796
00:25:53,127 --> 00:25:54,267
- that is shooting us.
- through the camera.

797
00:25:54,267 --> 00:25:55,627
But if you stand up,

798
00:25:55,627 --> 00:25:57,067
- your head will get cut out.
- It will get cut out.

799
00:25:57,067 --> 00:25:58,167
So I kept making him sit down.

800
00:25:58,167 --> 00:25:59,767
I should be careful. But I don't get cut when I stand up.

801
00:25:59,767 --> 00:26:00,837
It's okay.

802
00:26:01,437 --> 00:26:02,837
- That's right.
- For us...

803
00:26:02,837 --> 00:26:04,377
- It's okay for him.
- For me and Soo Geun,

804
00:26:04,377 --> 00:26:05,707
- it doesn't matter, - He really can fit.

805
00:26:05,707 --> 00:26:06,877
no matter what we do.

806
00:26:06,877 --> 00:26:08,347
- It's fine for them.
- Right?

807
00:26:08,347 --> 00:26:09,577
How low does it get?

808
00:26:09,577 --> 00:26:11,617
- He's always within the angle.
- Yes.

809
00:26:11,617 --> 00:26:13,247
You’re a god-given commentator.

810
00:26:13,247 --> 00:26:14,247
That's right.

811
00:26:15,817 --> 00:26:19,157
Seung Hi, I heard that your nickname...

812
00:26:19,157 --> 00:26:20,687
used to be "the tough guy for China."

813
00:26:20,687 --> 00:26:21,927
Yes.

814
00:26:21,927 --> 00:26:23,357
She really was the tough guy for China.

815
00:26:23,357 --> 00:26:24,357
What does that mean?

816
00:26:24,357 --> 00:26:27,267
We had an extremely intense...

817
00:26:27,267 --> 00:26:29,397
- rivalry with the Chinese players.
- Sure.

818
00:26:29,397 --> 00:26:30,937
- In the past.
- It was always like that.

819
00:26:30,937 --> 00:26:33,067
One time, I was sick of it,

820
00:26:33,067 --> 00:26:34,337
so as I was going to the track...

821
00:26:34,337 --> 00:26:38,637
There's a really famous skater in China, Wang Meng.

822
00:26:38,637 --> 00:26:39,947
She was the best for a long time.

823
00:26:39,947 --> 00:26:43,017
I had a fight with her in the ice rink.

824
00:26:43,747 --> 00:26:46,277
If you see the video clip, it looks like we're swearing.

825
00:26:46,277 --> 00:26:47,647
I saw it happen, and...

826
00:26:47,647 --> 00:26:48,717
He saw it from the side.

827
00:26:48,717 --> 00:26:51,587
You could tell that they were fighting right there.

828
00:26:51,587 --> 00:26:53,957
- Everyone came running to us.
- We were all worried,

829
00:26:53,957 --> 00:26:55,587
and we ran up to stop them.

830
00:26:55,587 --> 00:26:56,927
Since we had to stop the fight.

831
00:26:56,927 --> 00:26:59,197
We went up, and it was really petty...

832
00:26:59,197 --> 00:27:00,497
- and childish.
- We fought nicely.

833
00:27:01,067 --> 00:27:02,397
"Why are you using your hands?"

834
00:27:02,397 --> 00:27:03,637
"If you use your hands, it's dangerous for me."

835
00:27:03,637 --> 00:27:05,097
- That's how she was fighting.
- Yes.

836
00:27:05,097 --> 00:27:07,137
And it was the same with the Chinese athlete.

837
00:27:07,137 --> 00:27:08,967
But the important thing is, I was using Korean,

838
00:27:08,967 --> 00:27:10,977
and she was using Chinese.

839
00:27:11,507 --> 00:27:13,077
- They were exchanging emotions.
- We can feel it, though.

840
00:27:13,077 --> 00:27:14,947
She's mad, and I'm mad.

841
00:27:14,947 --> 00:27:16,477
We could only feel the emotions,

842
00:27:16,477 --> 00:27:18,677
but if you see the video, it looks very intense.

843
00:27:18,677 --> 00:27:21,947
Then they stopped us, so it was over.

844
00:27:21,947 --> 00:27:25,817
If a former athlete becomes a commentator,

845
00:27:25,957 --> 00:27:28,227
I think you would be more emotionally engaged than others.

846
00:27:28,227 --> 00:27:30,327
- It should be so much more.
- It must feel like you're there,

847
00:27:30,327 --> 00:27:31,997
- and when they are being unfair...
- Yes.

848
00:27:31,997 --> 00:27:34,267
When it wasn't foul play, but the referee said so.

849
00:27:34,627 --> 00:27:36,797
I think that would be the hard part.

850
00:27:36,797 --> 00:27:38,637
The perspective of an athlete...

851
00:27:38,637 --> 00:27:41,207
- And the viewers.
- and that of the viewers...

852
00:27:41,207 --> 00:27:43,007
could be completely different.

853
00:27:43,007 --> 00:27:45,007
- What do you think, as the viewer?
- When it becomes emotional.

854
00:27:45,007 --> 00:27:46,777
- Do you like it when we get mad?
- We swear while watching TV.

855
00:27:46,777 --> 00:27:47,847
- Sure.
- Yes.

856
00:27:47,847 --> 00:27:48,847
- Really?
- We get mad, as well.

857
00:27:48,847 --> 00:27:50,617
And you need to do the swearing for us, Yoon Gy.

858
00:27:50,617 --> 00:27:52,017
- The swearing?
- Sure.

859
00:27:52,017 --> 00:27:53,017
- I told him to try swearing.
- That's what we need.

860
00:27:53,017 --> 00:27:55,387
You need to think of it as your last time.

861
00:27:55,817 --> 00:27:57,087
How long do you expect to do that?

862
00:27:57,087 --> 00:27:59,057
And for us,

863
00:27:59,057 --> 00:28:02,527
we don't really know if the judge is being fair...

864
00:28:02,527 --> 00:28:04,157
or not.

865
00:28:04,497 --> 00:28:06,667
- So we rely on the commentators.
- That's how we know.

866
00:28:06,667 --> 00:28:07,667
Then what should we have done then?

867
00:28:07,667 --> 00:28:10,467
During the Beijing Winter Games,

868
00:28:10,467 --> 00:28:13,067
since Seung Hi was the tough guy for China...

869
00:28:13,307 --> 00:28:16,837
At first, there were some unfair rulings.

870
00:28:16,837 --> 00:28:18,477
- Since it was held in Beijing.
- Yes.

871
00:28:18,477 --> 00:28:21,007
- We got so mad, - Yes.

872
00:28:21,007 --> 00:28:23,677
but during those times, they weren't saying anything.

873
00:28:24,017 --> 00:28:25,517
- We just become speechless.
- It seemed like they couldn't...

874
00:28:25,517 --> 00:28:27,717
- vent out their emotions, - Yes.

875
00:28:27,717 --> 00:28:28,817
but just held it in.

876
00:28:28,817 --> 00:28:30,857
So I had to do all the talking.

877
00:28:30,857 --> 00:28:32,957
Did you ever lose your temper, Seong Jae?

878
00:28:33,327 --> 00:28:34,357
I do sometimes,

879
00:28:34,357 --> 00:28:36,257
- but I still...
- Can you control it?

880
00:28:36,257 --> 00:28:38,197
I think he thinks of it as someone else's problem.

881
00:28:38,197 --> 00:28:39,557
- Is that why?
- That's why...

882
00:28:39,557 --> 00:28:41,797
- He just needs to get paid.
- That's what it feels like.

883
00:28:41,797 --> 00:28:44,397
That's how he thinks of it, so he can control it better than us.

884
00:28:44,397 --> 00:28:46,937
- That's what it's like.
- But what about this?

885
00:28:46,937 --> 00:28:49,237
Since you used to be an athlete,

886
00:28:49,237 --> 00:28:51,037
can't you get into it emotionally and say,

887
00:28:51,037 --> 00:28:53,007
"I can't accept this."

888
00:28:53,007 --> 00:28:54,447
Can't you do that?

889
00:28:58,017 --> 00:29:00,517
- What does that mean?
- I didn't understand it.

890
00:29:00,517 --> 00:29:01,887
- I didn't understand...
- I didn't understand...

891
00:29:01,887 --> 00:29:03,217
what you were saying. what you were saying.

892
00:29:03,217 --> 00:29:04,617
- What was that?
- What are you saying?

893
00:29:04,617 --> 00:29:05,887
Get up and say it again.

894
00:29:05,887 --> 00:29:07,387
- He won the Grand Prize.
- Ask them.

895
00:29:07,387 --> 00:29:09,727
It's a very sophisticated question.

896
00:29:09,727 --> 00:29:11,957
- You may be the commentator, - Yes.

897
00:29:11,957 --> 00:29:13,867
but you can't get mad.

898
00:29:13,867 --> 00:29:15,167
But when you do get mad,

899
00:29:15,167 --> 00:29:16,967
just get into your emotions.

900
00:29:16,967 --> 00:29:18,597
"If I were that athlete,"

901
00:29:18,597 --> 00:29:20,207
"and if I were skating there,"

902
00:29:20,207 --> 00:29:23,107
- If it were me?
- "I wouldn't have accepted it."

903
00:29:23,107 --> 00:29:25,107
"I believe that this ruling was wrong."

904
00:29:25,107 --> 00:29:26,547
"However, as a commentator,"

905
00:29:26,547 --> 00:29:28,847
"I don't know how to put it."

906
00:29:28,847 --> 00:29:31,477
- Can't you say that?
- That's a very good comment.

907
00:29:31,477 --> 00:29:32,577
- It really is.
- It's about self-expression.

908
00:29:32,577 --> 00:29:33,887
- That's the model answer.
- I learned one today.

909
00:29:33,887 --> 00:29:35,087
- Yes.
- I should write that down.

910
00:29:35,087 --> 00:29:36,917
Phrasing your emotions indirectly.

911
00:29:36,917 --> 00:29:37,917
- You should use that.
- I will.

912
00:29:37,917 --> 00:29:39,117
"If it were me."

913
00:29:39,117 --> 00:29:41,457
Get into the emotions.

914
00:29:41,457 --> 00:29:43,427
That's a good one.

915
00:29:43,427 --> 00:29:44,657
Then what about...

916
00:29:44,827 --> 00:29:47,567
if a younger athlete was doing so badly?

917
00:29:47,827 --> 00:29:49,127
But that's not their usual performance.

918
00:29:49,527 --> 00:29:51,397
Do you usually confront them later,

919
00:29:51,397 --> 00:29:53,267
or do you...

920
00:29:53,267 --> 00:29:55,167
Since they must be all close to you.

921
00:29:55,167 --> 00:29:56,807
Even if the results were underwhelming,

922
00:29:56,807 --> 00:29:58,577
I don't think I can confront them.

923
00:29:58,577 --> 00:30:01,547
Because that's not up to me to tell them.

924
00:30:01,547 --> 00:30:02,977
They already have their coaches...

925
00:30:02,977 --> 00:30:04,977
- and many other team members.
- That's right.

926
00:30:04,977 --> 00:30:06,177
- It just becomes a lecture.
- So...

927
00:30:06,177 --> 00:30:07,347
they have them for that.

928
00:30:07,347 --> 00:30:09,017
- What we can do is...
- We say it while commentating.

929
00:30:09,017 --> 00:30:10,357
- Yes.
- During the commentating.

930
00:30:10,357 --> 00:30:12,257
We just tell them, "You're doing well."

931
00:30:12,257 --> 00:30:14,157
- Give them courage and faith.
- Yes.

932
00:30:14,157 --> 00:30:16,627
I'm sure you've met many commentators,

933
00:30:16,627 --> 00:30:17,997
but were there people who lost their temper?

934
00:30:17,997 --> 00:30:19,297
Those who couldn't keep it in?

935
00:30:19,597 --> 00:30:22,227
During the Jakarta Asian Games,

936
00:30:22,227 --> 00:30:23,737
Coach Choi Yong Soo...

937
00:30:24,197 --> 00:30:26,297
He was a coach, and it was his first time as a commentator,

938
00:30:26,297 --> 00:30:29,307
so he was only used to being on the field.

939
00:30:29,837 --> 00:30:31,007
Even when he was a coach,

940
00:30:31,007 --> 00:30:32,477
if a player made a mistake,

941
00:30:32,777 --> 00:30:35,707
he would keep looking at him until he made eye contact.

942
00:30:35,947 --> 00:30:37,477
Because he had to scold them.

943
00:30:37,477 --> 00:30:39,777
- So he would keep watching.
- He would be staring at him.

944
00:30:39,777 --> 00:30:42,187
He kept watching even if the ball was spinning.

945
00:30:42,587 --> 00:30:44,387
But even when he was commentating, someone made a mistake,

946
00:30:44,387 --> 00:30:45,987
and he kept watching that player.

947
00:30:45,987 --> 00:30:48,287
- He wouldn't even say a thing.
- Right.

948
00:30:48,287 --> 00:30:50,027
- Coach Choi Yong Soo?
- Yes.

949
00:30:50,027 --> 00:30:51,327
Why did he do that?

950
00:30:51,327 --> 00:30:52,727
- He's no joke.
- So I had to...

951
00:30:52,727 --> 00:30:53,967
I'm close to him.

952
00:30:53,967 --> 00:30:56,167
I had to nudge him to keep talking.

953
00:30:56,167 --> 00:30:57,667
"The ball is over here, so look here."

954
00:30:57,667 --> 00:31:00,167
But he kept watching that player.

955
00:31:00,307 --> 00:31:02,467
- He had the original Eagle Shoot.
- Yes.

956
00:31:02,467 --> 00:31:03,737
- That's right.
- But then...

957
00:31:04,437 --> 00:31:06,107
There must be people who cry too much.

958
00:31:06,107 --> 00:31:07,847
Those who become too emotional.

959
00:31:07,847 --> 00:31:10,217
Those who can't talk because of their tears.

960
00:31:10,217 --> 00:31:11,947
- Those who cry?
- I think I was like that.

961
00:31:11,947 --> 00:31:13,887
I know. Seung Hi is a bit soft-hearted.

962
00:31:13,887 --> 00:31:16,217
During the Beijing Olympics,

963
00:31:16,217 --> 00:31:17,817
- in the beginning, - It was going so badly.

964
00:31:17,817 --> 00:31:19,257
- the judgements were so unfair, - Yes.

965
00:31:19,257 --> 00:31:21,327
so she had pent-up emotions.

966
00:31:21,327 --> 00:31:22,987
But at the 1500m,

967
00:31:23,357 --> 00:31:25,257
- The gold medal.
- we won the gold medal,

968
00:31:25,257 --> 00:31:26,457
and she cried.

969
00:31:26,457 --> 00:31:27,627
I didn't think that would happen.

970
00:31:27,627 --> 00:31:28,927
- Not much different from Ho Dong.
- I got really choked up,

971
00:31:28,927 --> 00:31:30,797
- Right.
- so my voice wouldn't come out.

972
00:31:30,797 --> 00:31:32,537
- Later on?
- I almost became like Ho Dong.

973
00:31:32,537 --> 00:31:34,267
- That's so...
- "Like Ho Dong?"

974
00:31:34,267 --> 00:31:35,667
It was a close call.

975
00:31:35,667 --> 00:31:38,337
Rather than the comments,

976
00:31:38,337 --> 00:31:41,647
sometimes, the silence could be greater.

977
00:31:41,647 --> 00:31:44,317
- That shouldn't happen.
- It will be popular in 2026.

978
00:31:44,317 --> 00:31:45,417
If something doesn't work out,

979
00:31:45,417 --> 00:31:46,817
"I almost became like Ho Dong."

980
00:31:46,817 --> 00:31:48,417
("I almost became like Ho Dong.")

981
00:31:48,417 --> 00:31:50,557
- "It was a close call."
- "I almost became like Ho Dong."

982
00:31:50,557 --> 00:31:53,287
The response was positive during the Sochi Olympics.

983
00:31:53,287 --> 00:31:54,457
It was a hot topic.

984
00:31:54,457 --> 00:31:55,757
- I should watch it again.
- I saw it too.

985
00:31:55,757 --> 00:31:57,627
- It was famous.
- Yoon Gy, don't be like Ho Dong.

986
00:31:57,627 --> 00:31:58,927
- Okay.
- I saw it too.

987
00:31:58,927 --> 00:32:00,127
I saw it too.

988
00:32:00,127 --> 00:32:01,397
- He doesn't watch anything.
- At that time...

989
00:32:01,397 --> 00:32:02,797
KBS was in the middle,

990
00:32:02,797 --> 00:32:04,197
MBC was on the right,

991
00:32:04,197 --> 00:32:06,137
and SBS was on the other side.

992
00:32:06,137 --> 00:32:08,637
It was really cramped because of Ho Dong.

993
00:32:09,167 --> 00:32:10,477
(Shy)

994
00:32:10,477 --> 00:32:12,477
- He was taking up both sides.
- He's this big.

995
00:32:12,477 --> 00:32:14,147
We were sitting like this.

996
00:32:14,147 --> 00:32:15,507
- Could you hear them?
- What?

997
00:32:15,507 --> 00:32:17,247
- Was it soundproofed?
- You can hear everything.

998
00:32:17,247 --> 00:32:18,477
- You can hear everything?
- You can hear the sounds.

999
00:32:18,477 --> 00:32:22,147
I was shouting too much during the Beijing Olympics,

1000
00:32:22,147 --> 00:32:24,257
so they said their microphones were catching my voice.

1001
00:32:24,257 --> 00:32:26,287
You could hear Seong Jae's voice from other broadcasts.

1002
00:32:26,287 --> 00:32:27,427
Really?

1003
00:32:27,427 --> 00:32:30,057
My voice was in the other Korean broadcasts,

1004
00:32:30,057 --> 00:32:31,927
but also the foreign broadcasts.

1005
00:32:31,927 --> 00:32:33,567
The people in Canada heard my voice.

1006
00:32:34,397 --> 00:32:35,697
- That's good.
- It was so big.

1007
00:32:35,697 --> 00:32:38,237
It was during COVID-19,

1008
00:32:38,237 --> 00:32:40,967
so they stacked up acrylic boards next to me.

1009
00:32:40,967 --> 00:32:43,677
Seong Jae, but with you,

1010
00:32:43,677 --> 00:32:45,177
when you talk or commentate,

1011
00:32:45,177 --> 00:32:46,707
- we need to hear you, right?
- Yes.

1012
00:32:46,707 --> 00:32:48,677
But with you, I can see the words.

1013
00:32:48,877 --> 00:32:50,217
- Do you see the words?
- Yes.

1014
00:32:50,477 --> 00:32:52,177
- What's your secret?
- Your pronunciation is excellent.

1015
00:32:52,177 --> 00:32:54,487
I need to have good diction,

1016
00:32:54,487 --> 00:32:56,487
so I read a lot of newspapers.

1017
00:32:56,487 --> 00:32:57,687
- You read out loud?
- Yes.

1018
00:32:57,687 --> 00:32:58,757
I read out loud.

1019
00:32:58,757 --> 00:33:01,127
And you always bring around Hong Jin Ho...

1020
00:33:01,127 --> 00:33:03,427
so that your diction sounds better.

1021
00:33:03,797 --> 00:33:05,757
You always stick with Jin Ho.

1022
00:33:05,757 --> 00:33:07,397
- That's right.
- Why is Jin Ho's diction bad?

1023
00:33:07,397 --> 00:33:09,827
You can't understand Jin Ho even with the captions.

1024
00:33:11,037 --> 00:33:13,567
You can't understand him.

1025
00:33:14,407 --> 00:33:15,937
Jin Ho is so funny.

1026
00:33:15,937 --> 00:33:17,007
Even if he just reads, it's funny.

1027
00:33:17,007 --> 00:33:18,077
Yes.

1028
00:33:18,077 --> 00:33:19,737
- Yoon Gy.
- Yoon Gy.

1029
00:33:19,977 --> 00:33:22,747
For Yoon Gy, give him a round of applause.

1030
00:33:22,747 --> 00:33:24,517
- He wrote, "rookie commentator."
- You are a rookie.

1031
00:33:24,517 --> 00:33:26,447
Thank you.

1032
00:33:26,447 --> 00:33:27,587
That's amazing.

1033
00:33:27,587 --> 00:33:31,817
He was an Olympic athlete his whole life,

1034
00:33:31,817 --> 00:33:33,857
and now, he is the commentator.

1035
00:33:34,457 --> 00:33:36,257
It must be an honor,

1036
00:33:36,257 --> 00:33:38,357
- and a burden at the same time.
- Right. It must be a burden.

1037
00:33:38,357 --> 00:33:41,497
Well, it hasn't been long since I retired,

1038
00:33:41,897 --> 00:33:44,097
so I'm worried that I might speak too much...

1039
00:33:44,097 --> 00:33:45,237
from the athlete’s perspective.

1040
00:33:45,667 --> 00:33:47,437
I might be too much on the athlete's side.

1041
00:33:47,437 --> 00:33:48,767
I heard you've been preparing a lot.

1042
00:33:48,767 --> 00:33:50,777
What is this special preparation?

1043
00:33:50,777 --> 00:33:53,477
I need to see a lot of athletes...

1044
00:33:53,807 --> 00:33:56,347
in order to read the match well,

1045
00:33:56,547 --> 00:34:00,417
so I went to different international matches to watch them,

1046
00:34:00,417 --> 00:34:02,487
and had conversations with many athletes.

1047
00:34:02,487 --> 00:34:04,917
I studied them in a very immersive way.

1048
00:34:04,917 --> 00:34:05,917
(He worked hard to study on-site in order to help his commentating.)

1049
00:34:05,917 --> 00:34:08,457
I thought it would help with my commentating.

1050
00:34:08,457 --> 00:34:10,657
And the Olympics will be held in Milan,

1051
00:34:10,657 --> 00:34:13,727
so I visited the site beforehand...

1052
00:34:13,727 --> 00:34:14,827
and studied the vibe.

1053
00:34:14,827 --> 00:34:17,267
He went to the site beforehand.

1054
00:34:18,137 --> 00:34:21,337
(The short-track arena)

1055
00:34:21,767 --> 00:34:25,537
(The field where the opening ceremony will take place)

1056
00:34:26,037 --> 00:34:28,777
(He even met the mascot beforehand.)

1057
00:34:29,977 --> 00:34:31,217
Did you go with your own money?

1058
00:34:31,477 --> 00:34:33,017
Yes, I invested in it.

1059
00:34:33,017 --> 00:34:34,917
- Your own money?
- That's very cool.

1060
00:34:34,917 --> 00:34:36,987
This is what I think...

1061
00:34:36,987 --> 00:34:38,357
as a viewer.

1062
00:34:38,357 --> 00:34:41,587
One of those sports I stay up all night to watch...

1063
00:34:41,787 --> 00:34:43,957
just like the World Cup is short track.

1064
00:34:44,397 --> 00:34:45,697
I'm saying this as a viewer.

1065
00:34:45,697 --> 00:34:48,967
- That's right.
- The sport itself is very tense.

1066
00:34:49,127 --> 00:34:51,337
It all ends in the blink of an eye and it's nerve-racking.

1067
00:34:51,597 --> 00:34:54,067
- That's very touching.
- That's right.

1068
00:34:54,307 --> 00:34:56,367
At every Winter Games, we always say...

1069
00:34:56,607 --> 00:34:58,207
that short track has really leveled up overall.

1070
00:34:58,207 --> 00:34:59,277
- That's right.
- It has leveled up.

1071
00:34:59,277 --> 00:35:00,907
We always say that.

1072
00:35:01,077 --> 00:35:02,577
But this time, it's really true.

1073
00:35:02,777 --> 00:35:04,917
- That's right.
- This time, in the 1,500m,

1074
00:35:04,917 --> 00:35:07,017
Korea's strongest event,

1075
00:35:07,447 --> 00:35:09,317
there were four world tours so far.

1076
00:35:09,547 --> 00:35:12,187
Canada won three times,

1077
00:35:12,587 --> 00:35:14,487
and Korea won once.

1078
00:35:14,887 --> 00:35:16,157
- Before, - Canada became really strong.

1079
00:35:16,157 --> 00:35:18,757
- That's right.
- Korea would have won three times.

1080
00:35:18,957 --> 00:35:20,727
This time, things have changed,

1081
00:35:20,727 --> 00:35:23,567
and we're a little worried as well.

1082
00:35:23,567 --> 00:35:25,767
Who are the speed skaters we should pay attention to?

1083
00:35:25,997 --> 00:35:27,207
Speed skaters to pay attention to?

1084
00:35:27,207 --> 00:35:29,807
I also stepped down this time,

1085
00:35:30,007 --> 00:35:32,407
and there was a complete generational transition.

1086
00:35:32,507 --> 00:35:34,007
- The skaters to pay attention to.
- I was...

1087
00:35:34,007 --> 00:35:35,447
- a very old speed skater.
- Really?

1088
00:35:35,447 --> 00:35:37,877
Even when I was active,

1089
00:35:37,877 --> 00:35:39,877
I was more than ten years older than the others.

1090
00:35:40,147 --> 00:35:42,817
The generational transition wasn't complete because of me,

1091
00:35:43,017 --> 00:35:45,687
- but I...
- People have to leave quickly.

1092
00:35:45,687 --> 00:35:48,657
- Yes. I stayed there too long.
- You're like Kang Ho Dong.

1093
00:35:48,657 --> 00:35:51,327
He has to leave for the next generation to rise.

1094
00:35:51,327 --> 00:35:53,457
- I was there for too long.
- Trying to stay until the very end.

1095
00:35:54,027 --> 00:35:55,567
- Was it like that?
- It was.

1096
00:35:55,667 --> 00:35:56,667
(Is he talking about me?)

1097
00:35:56,667 --> 00:35:57,937
I get what you mean.

1098
00:35:58,237 --> 00:35:59,267
It makes perfect sense.

1099
00:35:59,267 --> 00:36:00,637
You have to leave quickly.

1100
00:36:00,737 --> 00:36:02,867
This time, the generational transition was complete.

1101
00:36:03,237 --> 00:36:07,347
The youngest skater is Rim Jong Un.

1102
00:36:07,347 --> 00:36:09,547
- He's so talented.
- I was...

1103
00:36:09,777 --> 00:36:10,817
He was born in 2007.

1104
00:36:10,817 --> 00:36:12,117
at the national team trials with him.

1105
00:36:12,277 --> 00:36:13,987
- He's just turned an adult.
- That's right.

1106
00:36:14,287 --> 00:36:15,487
- Were you nice to him?
- Seriously.

1107
00:36:15,487 --> 00:36:17,417
We were at the national team trials together.

1108
00:36:17,417 --> 00:36:19,457
I made my debut in 2007.

1109
00:36:19,687 --> 00:36:21,487
- My world stage debut was in 2007.
- That's right.

1110
00:36:21,487 --> 00:36:24,397
When I made my debut, I never imagined...

1111
00:36:24,397 --> 00:36:26,897
I would be at the national team trials with someone born in 2007.

1112
00:36:26,897 --> 00:36:28,797
While competing with him,

1113
00:36:28,867 --> 00:36:30,837
I thought I should really quit.

1114
00:36:30,997 --> 00:36:34,167
His speed is on a whole different level.

1115
00:36:34,737 --> 00:36:35,907
He's really fast.

1116
00:36:35,907 --> 00:36:42,777
(Yoon Gy and Jong Un)

1117
00:36:42,777 --> 00:36:45,177
His outside pass was incredibly fast.

1118
00:36:45,577 --> 00:36:47,517
I just couldn't stop him.

1119
00:36:47,517 --> 00:36:49,987
When I played ssireum before,

1120
00:36:50,557 --> 00:36:51,817
I would just go to a certain arena,

1121
00:36:51,817 --> 00:36:53,987
and it just felt easy and warm.

1122
00:36:54,157 --> 00:36:55,757
That's when you get the Chunha ssireum champion.

1123
00:36:55,757 --> 00:36:56,827
You definitely get that feeling.

1124
00:36:56,927 --> 00:36:59,097
But some arenas...

1125
00:36:59,097 --> 00:37:00,597
would just feel cold and intimidating.

1126
00:37:00,597 --> 00:37:02,467
- That's right.
- Do you feel that?

1127
00:37:02,467 --> 00:37:03,497
That happens.

1128
00:37:03,497 --> 00:37:05,767
Yeong Cheol is funny in all the other channels,

1129
00:37:05,767 --> 00:37:07,167
- but when he's here...
- It doesn't work out for him here.

1130
00:37:07,707 --> 00:37:09,067
- I wonder why.
- He's not funny here.

1131
00:37:09,337 --> 00:37:10,977
- There are such places.
- Should we change the studio?

1132
00:37:10,977 --> 00:37:12,577
In other places...

1133
00:37:12,577 --> 00:37:15,977
I laugh at what he says in shows like "Pinggyego."

1134
00:37:15,977 --> 00:37:17,277
He's good in "Pinggyego,"

1135
00:37:17,277 --> 00:37:18,777
- but whenever he's here...
- That's weird.

1136
00:37:18,777 --> 00:37:20,147
- I wonder why.
- I guess that's what it feels like.

1137
00:37:20,317 --> 00:37:23,547
In the Vancouver Winter Games, I was young.

1138
00:37:23,547 --> 00:37:26,417
The arena was the same size,

1139
00:37:26,417 --> 00:37:27,657
but it looked huge.

1140
00:37:27,657 --> 00:37:29,187
So I was a little intimidated...

1141
00:37:29,187 --> 00:37:31,427
even before I entered.

1142
00:37:31,527 --> 00:37:32,597
- Internally.
- That happens.

1143
00:37:32,857 --> 00:37:34,897
In Sochi, I had that feeling.

1144
00:37:34,897 --> 00:37:36,127
Every athlete would know it.

1145
00:37:36,297 --> 00:37:38,337
When you step onto the rink for warm-ups,

1146
00:37:38,337 --> 00:37:40,167
there's that feeling you get when your blade...

1147
00:37:40,607 --> 00:37:42,607
- just moves forward smoothly.
- Is it because of the ice quality?

1148
00:37:42,607 --> 00:37:44,937
When the ice quality and my condition are excellent.

1149
00:37:44,937 --> 00:37:46,937
I felt that in Sochi.

1150
00:37:46,937 --> 00:37:48,407
- My feet just glided forward.
- It was totally...

1151
00:37:48,777 --> 00:37:50,147
- It's...
- I guess every athlete feels that.

1152
00:37:50,147 --> 00:37:51,917
I heard Seung Hi...

1153
00:37:52,047 --> 00:37:55,347
- had a medal for all the events.
- That's right.

1154
00:37:55,517 --> 00:37:56,647
- That's right.
- That's the first ever.

1155
00:37:56,647 --> 00:37:57,957
- That's so cool.
- Please clap for me.

1156
00:37:58,557 --> 00:37:59,587
(You're amazing, Park Seung Hi.)

1157
00:37:59,587 --> 00:38:00,957
You have the medals for every event?

1158
00:38:01,087 --> 00:38:03,287
In women's short track, I'm the only one...

1159
00:38:03,527 --> 00:38:05,627
to have won medals in every event.

1160
00:38:05,957 --> 00:38:06,957
- She's legendary.
- Yes.

1161
00:38:06,957 --> 00:38:09,067
I'm also the only athlete to have competed...

1162
00:38:09,067 --> 00:38:10,737
in the world sporting events in two different events.

1163
00:38:10,837 --> 00:38:13,807
- She also did speed skating.
- That's right.

1164
00:38:14,107 --> 00:38:15,967
Seung Hi is really amazing.

1165
00:38:16,367 --> 00:38:18,837
People who are good at short distances...

1166
00:38:18,977 --> 00:38:20,477
aren't good at long distance races.

1167
00:38:20,677 --> 00:38:22,307
Seung Hi is the only one...

1168
00:38:22,707 --> 00:38:24,277
who is good at both short...

1169
00:38:24,277 --> 00:38:25,847
- and long distance races.
- She's an all-rounder.

1170
00:38:25,847 --> 00:38:26,847
- An all-rounder.
- That's amazing.

1171
00:38:26,847 --> 00:38:28,617
Seong Jae. Sportscasters...

1172
00:38:29,087 --> 00:38:30,987
- are mostly announcers.
- Yes.

1173
00:38:31,157 --> 00:38:32,817
Do you have to be an announcer to be a sportscaster?

1174
00:38:32,987 --> 00:38:35,787
Can't you do it if you talk well and have knowledge...

1175
00:38:35,787 --> 00:38:38,197
- in sports?
- So far, they were all announcers.

1176
00:38:38,597 --> 00:38:41,467
But later, I think anyone here could do it.

1177
00:38:41,467 --> 00:38:43,767
But it's hard to break a long-standing tradition.

1178
00:38:43,767 --> 00:38:45,167
- I'm sorry, - Yeong Cheol is...

1179
00:38:45,167 --> 00:38:46,567
but why did you ask that question?

1180
00:38:46,667 --> 00:38:47,837
- I...
- He wants to be a sportscaster.

1181
00:38:47,967 --> 00:38:50,707
I watched a lot of games commentated by Bang Sang Ah...

1182
00:38:50,707 --> 00:38:52,307
- and Bae Ki Wan.
- Yes.

1183
00:38:52,437 --> 00:38:55,777
I watched all of Kim Yu Na's competitions.

1184
00:38:56,077 --> 00:38:57,617
So I memorized all the figure skating terms...

1185
00:38:57,617 --> 00:38:59,977
like triple lutz, toe loop, and so on.

1186
00:38:59,977 --> 00:39:02,347
- But doesn't he talk too much?
- He does.

1187
00:39:02,347 --> 00:39:04,517
But for figure skating,

1188
00:39:04,687 --> 00:39:06,387
- there isn't much sound.
- It has to be calm.

1189
00:39:06,387 --> 00:39:08,187
It's more important to deliver the emotions.

1190
00:39:08,187 --> 00:39:09,987
Right. Figure skating commentaries weren't so chatty.

1191
00:39:10,497 --> 00:39:12,327
Let's watch Seong Jae's commentary.

1192
00:39:12,457 --> 00:39:13,557
- Seon Jae's commentary.
- Okay.

1193
00:39:13,557 --> 00:39:14,997
- We have to be quiet.
- He'll demonstrate first.

1194
00:39:15,097 --> 00:39:16,167
- Demonstration.
- Seong Jae.

1195
00:39:16,167 --> 00:39:17,467
- Now...
- It's starting.

1196
00:39:17,467 --> 00:39:19,297
It's the women's 1,500m final!

1197
00:39:19,837 --> 00:39:20,907
Let's watch it.

1198
00:39:21,037 --> 00:39:22,037
Hello, everyone.

1199
00:39:22,037 --> 00:39:24,137
The Beijing Winter Games women's 1,500m final...

1200
00:39:24,137 --> 00:39:25,177
is underway right now.

1201
00:39:25,177 --> 00:39:27,277
- Choi Min Jeong is taking the lead.
- That's right.

1202
