- She's like a little sister.

1441
00:47:05,337 --> 00:47:07,437
Seung Hi, for your recent update,

1442
00:47:07,437 --> 00:47:09,707
you wrote, "All-rounder."

1443
00:47:09,707 --> 00:47:11,607
- Lately, you're on variety shows, - Right.

1444
00:47:11,607 --> 00:47:12,737
- and you run a business too.
- I do.

1445
00:47:12,737 --> 00:47:14,207
- And you're raising a child too.
- Yes.

1446
00:47:14,207 --> 00:47:15,607
- Gosh, isn't that hard?
- Do you run a business as well?

1447
00:47:15,607 --> 00:47:17,377
I think I have a knack...

1448
00:47:17,377 --> 00:47:20,277
for making things outside of doing sports.

1449
00:47:20,277 --> 00:47:23,717
Something like clothing? I like fashion too.

1450
00:47:23,847 --> 00:47:26,987
I've had that talent for a while, so I've always wanted to try it.

1451
00:47:27,287 --> 00:47:29,157
They're all hard, but what do you think?

1452
00:47:29,157 --> 00:47:31,757
Business, variety shows, and childcare.

1453
00:47:31,757 --> 00:47:32,827
Which one is the hardest?

1454
00:47:33,127 --> 00:47:35,667
- I think childcare is hard.
- Childcare is just...

1455
00:47:35,667 --> 00:47:39,337
It's really hard to raise a human being.

1456
00:47:39,337 --> 00:47:41,167
- And it doesn't go the way I want.
- Of course.

1457
00:47:41,167 --> 00:47:42,737
I think that's why childcare is the hardest.

1458
00:47:42,737 --> 00:47:44,207
(Childcare is hard, but it brings that much happiness.)

1459
00:47:44,437 --> 00:47:46,777
Seung Hi, does your whole family do sports on ice?

1460
00:47:46,977 --> 00:47:48,277
So, there are three of us.

1461
00:47:48,277 --> 00:47:51,917
My older sister and younger brother went to the Sochi Winter Games too.

1462
00:47:51,917 --> 00:47:53,647
My brother-in-law went to Vancouver...

1463
00:47:53,647 --> 00:47:55,847
with Yoon Gy as well.

1464
00:47:55,847 --> 00:47:56,887
(Her brother-in-law competed in the 2010 Vancouver Winter Games.)

1465
00:47:56,887 --> 00:47:58,817
- That's us. A sports family.
- Even your brother-in-law?

1466
00:47:58,817 --> 00:48:00,717
- My brother-in-law too.
- Your family does winter sports.

1467
00:48:00,717 --> 00:48:01,957
- That's true.
- We all do winter sports,

1468
00:48:01,957 --> 00:48:02,957
and we've all been to the Winter Games.

1469
00:48:02,957 --> 00:48:04,527
You were born into it.

1470
00:48:04,527 --> 00:48:05,627
They should build an ice rink.

1471
00:48:05,627 --> 00:48:07,667
Seriously, in 2014,

1472
00:48:07,667 --> 00:48:10,467
all three siblings qualifying for the national team was...

1473
00:48:10,467 --> 00:48:11,597
- Right.
- For real.

1474
00:48:11,597 --> 00:48:12,997
- It must've been a blessing.
- But...

1475
00:48:12,997 --> 00:48:14,907
when we took our ages into account,

1476
00:48:14,907 --> 00:48:18,107
that year, 2014, was the year we could go together.

1477
00:48:18,237 --> 00:48:20,707
So, we were all hoping it would happen,

1478
00:48:20,707 --> 00:48:23,847
and we were so grateful that we all made the team and went together.

1479
00:48:23,847 --> 00:48:26,377
The national team trials for short track is pretty much...

1480
00:48:26,377 --> 00:48:27,787
- Right.
- If you make the team,

1481
00:48:27,787 --> 00:48:29,117
- you can pretty much win a medal.
- Right.

1482
00:48:29,117 --> 00:48:30,717
- Yes, it was like that back then.
- At the time.

1483
00:48:30,717 --> 00:48:32,317
- Hey, Seung Hi.
- Yes?

1484
00:48:32,317 --> 00:48:35,287
- Yoon Gy competed for a long time.
- Yes.

1485
00:48:35,287 --> 00:48:39,297
But didn't you only actively compete for a short time?

1486
00:48:39,427 --> 00:48:40,527
It was short.

1487
00:48:40,527 --> 00:48:44,797
For short track, I retired...

1488
00:48:44,797 --> 00:48:46,197
- at 23 or 24.
- That's so young.

1489
00:48:46,197 --> 00:48:47,637
- Then, I switched sports.
- You retired so early.

1490
00:48:47,637 --> 00:48:50,237
I competed for another four years in speed skating.

1491
00:48:50,237 --> 00:48:53,677
Then, I retired for good at 27.

1492
00:48:53,677 --> 00:48:56,147
But back then, Yoon Gy tried to convince me to stay.

1493
00:48:56,147 --> 00:48:58,947
- He said, "Keep doing short track."
- Right.

1494
00:48:58,947 --> 00:49:00,947
But ever since I was really little,

1495
00:49:00,947 --> 00:49:04,417
I thought I'd retire as soon as I win a gold medal.

1496
00:49:04,417 --> 00:49:06,687
Then, why did you switch sports from doing short track?

1497
00:49:07,217 --> 00:49:10,257
I don't know if you all watched, but at Sochi, during the 500m,

1498
00:49:10,257 --> 00:49:13,327
I fell twice and missed out on winning the gold.

1499
00:49:13,597 --> 00:49:16,467
Then, I really doubted myself.

1500
00:49:16,567 --> 00:49:19,267
"Even if I work so hard to prepare,"

1501
00:49:19,267 --> 00:49:22,207
"this can happen because of someone else."

1502
00:49:22,207 --> 00:49:23,807
That weighed heavily on my mind.

1503
00:49:23,807 --> 00:49:26,437
So I decided to retire and took about five months off.

1504
00:49:26,437 --> 00:49:29,047
Since the Winter Games were going to be held in Pyeongchang,

1505
00:49:29,047 --> 00:49:30,677
I wanted to compete in it, no matter what.

1506
00:49:30,677 --> 00:49:32,117
But I didn't want to do short track anymore,

1507
00:49:32,117 --> 00:49:35,387
so I was thinking, "How can I compete?"

1508
00:49:35,387 --> 00:49:38,757
I found out no one had ever competed in two sports at the Winter Games.

1509
00:49:38,757 --> 00:49:40,457
"Oh, I should try this."

1510
00:49:40,457 --> 00:49:42,327
That's what I thought when I switched sports.

1511
00:49:42,527 --> 00:49:44,997
But I think I just had a strong spirit back then.

1512
00:49:44,997 --> 00:49:47,557
I felt like I could do it. I think that's how I was back then.

1513
00:49:47,557 --> 00:49:49,567
And I'm so grateful that I actually got to compete.

1514
00:49:50,127 --> 00:49:53,397
(Seung Hi was the first to compete in two sports at the Winter Games.)

1515
00:49:53,597 --> 00:49:55,937
All right. Lastly, Yoon Gy.

1516
00:49:56,337 --> 00:49:59,207
Your recent update is "Retirement."

1517
00:49:59,837 --> 00:50:01,147
How long has it been since you retired, Yoon Gy?

1518
00:50:01,407 --> 00:50:03,047
- I retired last April.
- It hasn't been that long.

1519
00:50:03,047 --> 00:50:04,377
- Right, it hasn't been very long.
- Not even a year.

1520
00:50:04,377 --> 00:50:05,677
- But...
- Last April.

1521
00:50:05,677 --> 00:50:08,017
many people who know Yoon Gy...

1522
00:50:08,147 --> 00:50:10,717
may think that you already retired...

1523
00:50:10,717 --> 00:50:12,317
- a long time ago.
- You're right.

1524
00:50:12,317 --> 00:50:13,687
- He competed for a long time.
- Right.

1525
00:50:13,687 --> 00:50:14,887
- As they watched you on YouTube...
- Yes.

1526
00:50:14,887 --> 00:50:18,057
Well, ever since the 2022 Beijing Winter Games,

1527
00:50:18,427 --> 00:50:20,257
since I am older than other players,

1528
00:50:20,457 --> 00:50:22,627
many people must've assumed that...

1529
00:50:22,627 --> 00:50:24,867
this was my last Winter Games.

1530
00:50:25,097 --> 00:50:26,897
But actually, as I kept going,

1531
00:50:27,197 --> 00:50:29,837
I was still aiming for the Milano Winter Games.

1532
00:50:30,007 --> 00:50:32,007
Also, Jang Hoon and Ho Dong,

1533
00:50:32,007 --> 00:50:34,747
who were athletes before, may know this.

1534
00:50:34,877 --> 00:50:37,747
When I thought about retiring, I felt scared.

1535
00:50:38,117 --> 00:50:39,677
"What will I do when I'm done competing?"

1536
00:50:40,177 --> 00:50:42,987
"If I'm not an athlete, who am I?"

1537
00:50:43,087 --> 00:50:45,287
Because of these thoughts, I felt so anxious...

1538
00:50:45,517 --> 00:50:46,817
that I couldn't work up the courage.

1539
00:50:46,817 --> 00:50:48,387
So I just kept dragging it on.

1540
00:50:48,387 --> 00:50:52,197
Then, the trials for the Milano Winter Games drew near.

1541
00:50:52,597 --> 00:50:54,697
I thought, "I should do my best up to this point."

1542
00:50:54,927 --> 00:50:56,827
- That's impressive.
- So that final month of April...

1543
00:50:56,867 --> 00:50:58,797
- was the period when...
- The trials.

1544
00:50:58,797 --> 00:51:00,437
I participated in trials for the Milano Winter Games.

1545
00:51:00,437 --> 00:51:02,567
Then, if you had been chosen,

1546
00:51:02,567 --> 00:51:04,507
you would have been going to Milan as an athlete, not a commentator.

1547
00:51:04,507 --> 00:51:05,537
- I could've gone as an athlete.
- Right.

1548
00:51:05,537 --> 00:51:07,107
Then he'd be in Milan right now.

1549
00:51:07,177 --> 00:51:08,307
That's awesome.

1550
00:51:08,347 --> 00:51:11,377
When you retire... I've never been a competitive athlete.

1551
00:51:11,577 --> 00:51:13,517
Then, does your daily life pattern change entirely?

1552
00:51:13,677 --> 00:51:14,887
At first... It totally changes.

1553
00:51:14,887 --> 00:51:17,117
We usually get up really early in the morning,

1554
00:51:17,117 --> 00:51:18,417
and we start training right away.

1555
00:51:18,987 --> 00:51:21,157
Since I don't have to do that anymore,

1556
00:51:21,157 --> 00:51:22,557
- it was so nice at first.
- It is nice.

1557
00:51:22,687 --> 00:51:23,687
I got to sleep in.

1558
00:51:23,687 --> 00:51:25,427
- You'll suddenly grow taller, then.
- So...

1559
00:51:26,727 --> 00:51:28,967
But why didn't I grow taller? I got plenty of sleep.

1560
00:51:28,967 --> 00:51:30,467
- That's odd.
- You'll be Jang Hoon's height soon.

1561
00:51:30,467 --> 00:51:31,497
- Right.
- But Yoon Gy...

1562
00:51:31,497 --> 00:51:32,537
Take good care of yourself.

1563
00:51:32,537 --> 00:51:33,797
- You might suddenly grow a lot.
- I don't.

1564
00:51:33,797 --> 00:51:35,467
- Do you sleep through the night?
- Your knees will get stretch marks.

1565
00:51:35,467 --> 00:51:36,467
I sleep so deeply...

1566
00:51:36,467 --> 00:51:37,667
- these days. Yes.
- Do you sleep deeply now?

1567
00:51:37,667 --> 00:51:38,907
You gain some weight at first, don't you?

1568
00:51:39,007 --> 00:51:41,577
I've already gained some weight. About 8kg.

1569
00:51:41,577 --> 00:51:43,007
- What, 8kg?
- This is you after gaining weight?

1570
00:51:43,007 --> 00:51:44,047
- I've gained 8kg.
- We can't tell.

1571
00:51:44,047 --> 00:51:45,077
- I didn't think you gained any.
- You don't exercise as much.

1572
00:51:45,077 --> 00:51:47,817
When I was still competing, I weighed about 62kg.

1573
00:51:47,817 --> 00:51:49,987
Now, I weigh almost 70kg.

1574
00:51:50,147 --> 00:51:52,387
I definitely gained weight since I started exercising less.

1575
00:51:52,387 --> 00:51:53,817
Since you retired in April,

1576
00:51:53,817 --> 00:51:55,257
- it hasn't been a full year yet.
- Yes.

1577
00:51:55,257 --> 00:51:56,987
Have you ever put on your ice skates?

1578
00:51:56,987 --> 00:51:58,657
I haven't put them on yet.

1579
00:51:58,957 --> 00:52:01,427
There hasn't been an occasion to put them on.

1580
00:52:01,927 --> 00:52:03,427
I purposefully distanced myself from them.

1581
00:52:03,427 --> 00:52:05,567
I didn't want to put them on as a joke...

1582
00:52:05,567 --> 00:52:07,967
and get the urge to go back to being an athlete.

1583
00:52:07,967 --> 00:52:10,667
Yoon Gy, you've won many medals.

1584
00:52:10,667 --> 00:52:12,277
- You run a YouTube channel.
- Yes.

1585
00:52:12,507 --> 00:52:14,007
Do you only have 1,000 dollars in your bank account?

1586
00:52:14,007 --> 00:52:16,207
- I'm sure he has another one.
- No way.

1587
00:52:16,207 --> 00:52:18,247
Seung Hi knows this, but short-track speed skaters...

1588
00:52:18,247 --> 00:52:19,817
- don't make a lot of money.
- That's right.

1589
00:52:19,817 --> 00:52:21,987
We use more money as athletes.

1590
00:52:21,987 --> 00:52:24,117
Our annual income is very low.

1591
00:52:24,117 --> 00:52:27,157
Despite that, it takes a lot of money to keep skating.

1592
00:52:27,287 --> 00:52:28,427
We need the gear...

1593
00:52:28,427 --> 00:52:29,987
- and suits.
- That's right. They're expensive.

1594
00:52:29,987 --> 00:52:31,597
We need to rent the ice skating rink.

1595
00:52:31,597 --> 00:52:33,597
- Those things take a lot of money.
- That's right.

1596
00:52:33,597 --> 00:52:36,097
The blade holders cost anywhere between 400 and 500 dollars.

1597
00:52:36,097 --> 00:52:39,637
Ice skate boots cost anywhere between 2,000 and 2,500 dollars.

1598
00:52:39,637 --> 00:52:43,067
Ice skate blades cost anywhere between 700 and 900 dollars.

1599
00:52:44,207 --> 00:52:48,107
(4,880 dollars in a year)

1600
00:52:48,347 --> 00:52:49,707
Thus, I didn't save up a lot of money.

1601
00:52:50,007 --> 00:52:51,947
- Oh, no.
- I see.

1602
00:52:52,017 --> 00:52:53,347
- They have no intention to help.
- Seriously.

1603
00:52:53,347 --> 00:52:54,787
They just said, "Oh, no."

1604
00:52:54,787 --> 00:52:56,517
- Still...
- Help us, guys.

1605
00:52:56,517 --> 00:52:58,487
Don't you run a YouTube channel...

1606
00:52:58,487 --> 00:53:00,457
- and a business?
- You run a YouTube channel.

1607
00:53:00,457 --> 00:53:02,787
As for the YouTube channel... I thought...

1608
00:53:02,787 --> 00:53:04,757
I'd make a lot of money if I had one million subscribers.

1609
00:53:04,757 --> 00:53:06,797
- It isn't like that these days.
- It wasn't like that.

1610
00:53:06,797 --> 00:53:07,857
- Are there one million subscribers?
- It all depends on view counts.

1611
00:53:07,857 --> 00:53:09,897
Soo Geun said something...

1612
00:53:10,127 --> 00:53:13,097
when I visited the show 4 years ago with over 1 million subscribers.

1613
00:53:13,097 --> 00:53:14,567
"That won't last long. The number will go down."

1614
00:53:14,567 --> 00:53:16,407
I remember him saying that.

1615
00:53:16,507 --> 00:53:17,767
(After the match,)

1616
00:53:17,767 --> 00:53:20,537
(the number of subscribers rose to 1.2 million.)

1617
00:53:20,537 --> 00:53:22,647
(They'll be gone by summer.)

1618
00:53:22,777 --> 00:53:25,817
- The bubble is bursting.
- My words were based on shamanism.

1619
00:53:25,817 --> 00:53:27,447
- He's a shaman.
- I can see everything.

1620
00:53:27,447 --> 00:53:30,687
- How suspicious.
- The last one is...

1621
00:53:31,147 --> 00:53:32,587
the three friends' future dream.

1622
00:53:32,587 --> 00:53:34,357
Even when you age,

1623
00:53:34,487 --> 00:53:36,657
- you can still have a future dream.
- That's right.

1624
00:53:36,657 --> 00:53:37,927
Firstly, Seong Jae wrote,

1625
00:53:38,757 --> 00:53:39,897
"Longevity."

1626
00:53:39,897 --> 00:53:40,957
Seong Jae, are you ill?

1627
00:53:40,957 --> 00:53:42,897
No, I'm not ill.

1628
00:53:43,097 --> 00:53:46,697
In the past, I didn't think about my lifespan.

1629
00:53:46,697 --> 00:53:48,107
But now that I'm married to someone...

1630
00:53:48,107 --> 00:53:49,567
- who is a lot younger...
- You got married.

1631
00:53:49,567 --> 00:53:50,937
My wife worries a lot too.

1632
00:53:50,937 --> 00:53:54,107
- Health.
- When she came over for a date,

1633
00:53:54,107 --> 00:53:55,877
I always ordered deliveries.

1634
00:53:55,877 --> 00:53:56,977
She was very startled.

1635
00:53:56,977 --> 00:54:00,277
She had never ordered a delivery.

1636
00:54:00,277 --> 00:54:03,717
She saw my tendencies and said, "Isn't this bad for your health?"

1637
00:54:03,717 --> 00:54:05,687
Does your wife cook for you?

1638
00:54:05,687 --> 00:54:09,357
She cooks light dishes using healthy ingredients.

1639
00:54:09,357 --> 00:54:11,287
It's like cooking for an athlete.

1640
00:54:11,287 --> 00:54:13,757
(She protects Seong Jae's health.)

1641
00:54:14,097 --> 00:54:16,297
You eat again outside after eating those meals at home, right?

1642
00:54:16,827 --> 00:54:17,827
How did you know?

1643
00:54:18,237 --> 00:54:20,537
- How did you know? You're good.
- Really?

1644
00:54:20,537 --> 00:54:23,067
Compared to the past, Seong Jae lost weight.

1645
00:54:23,067 --> 00:54:24,777
- That's right.
- After getting married,

1646
00:54:24,777 --> 00:54:25,807
I lost about 7kg.

1647
00:54:25,807 --> 00:54:27,677
- Exactly.
- Did you lose weight?

1648
00:54:27,907 --> 00:54:31,477
As his future goal, Yoon Gy wrote...

1649
00:54:31,477 --> 00:54:33,717
I don't know what you mean by this.

1650
00:54:33,717 --> 00:54:35,347
He wrote, "Seo Jang Hoon."

1651
00:54:35,347 --> 00:54:36,917
- Do you want to marry a tall woman?
- Tall height?

1652
00:54:36,917 --> 00:54:39,357
- Jang Hoon is a senior...
- Seo Jang Mi.

1653
00:54:39,357 --> 00:54:40,717
who graduated from my college.

1654
00:54:41,157 --> 00:54:42,887
He's tall.

1655
00:54:43,187 --> 00:54:47,397
He built an incredible career in sports.

1656
00:54:47,397 --> 00:54:48,927
He's really good at shows too.

1657
00:54:49,367 --> 00:54:50,667
I'm also jealous...

1658
00:54:50,667 --> 00:54:51,997
of his honesty.

1659
00:54:52,637 --> 00:54:55,007
He can speak his mind to people.

1660
00:54:55,007 --> 00:54:57,167
Since I'm not good at that,

1661
00:54:57,167 --> 00:54:58,307
I'm jealous.

1662
00:54:58,307 --> 00:55:00,477
Speaking one's mind isn't for everyone.

1663
00:55:00,477 --> 00:55:01,677
- It isn't for you.
- If you do it,

1664
00:55:01,677 --> 00:55:02,907
- you'll get into a fight.
- Personally...

1665
00:55:02,907 --> 00:55:04,747
Speaking one's mind without holding back...

1666
00:55:04,747 --> 00:55:05,977
is something you need to be born with.

1667
00:55:05,977 --> 00:55:07,117
- That's right.
- I agree.

1668
00:55:07,117 --> 00:55:08,247
- It isn't easy.
- If you copy it recklessly,

1669
00:55:08,247 --> 00:55:09,887
- you'll get an unpleasant surprise.
- I agree.

1670
00:55:09,887 --> 00:55:13,157
It isn't easy to be impatient.

1671
00:55:13,157 --> 00:55:14,617
I think there's only one in the world.

1672
00:55:14,617 --> 00:55:15,957
- There's only 1.
- Only 1 in the world.

1673
00:55:15,957 --> 00:55:17,987
- There he is.
- Only one in the world.

1674
00:55:17,987 --> 00:55:20,557
If you copy him, you'll get into trouble.

1675
00:55:20,557 --> 00:55:22,127
Don't copy something like this.

1676
00:55:22,127 --> 00:55:24,097
If you copy it, your fingers might get broken.

1677
00:55:24,197 --> 00:55:25,337
(Copy me if you can!)

1678
00:55:25,337 --> 00:55:26,697
All right. Seung Hi.

1679
00:55:26,697 --> 00:55:28,037
Seung Hi is next.

1680
